{"type":"message","id":"0a4f07c1","parentId":"d1396380","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:13:42.032Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the x402 pay-as-you-go implementation status for Parse agents. This is a specialist task involving code/builds/architecture, which should be routed to temujin according to AGENTS.md routing table.\n\nLet me check what I know from context:\n- Parse is deployed at parsethe.media\n- x402 payment integration is mentioned for Parse\n- There were TypeScript errors blocking new features\n\nI should route this to temujin since it's about:\n- Code/builds/APIs\n- Payment integration\n- Implementation status\n\nLet me send a message to temujin to get the current status.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Routing to temujin for x402 payment integration status."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7c4b039527b9444693deec67","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"temujin","message":"Human asks: What's the current status of the x402 pay-as-you-go implementation for Parse agents?\n\nContext from MEMORY.md:\n- Parse deployed at parsethe.media\n- x402 payment integration mentioned\n- TypeScript errors were blocking new features\n\nPlease provide:\n1. Current implementation status\n2. What's working vs what's pending\n3. Any blockers\n4. Next steps"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":5190,"output":246,"cacheRead":13952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19388,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772759608454}}
{"type":"message","id":"68c3e437","parentId":"0a4f07c1","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:13:42.063Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7c4b039527b9444693deec67","toolName":"message","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"message\",\n  \"error\": \"Unknown target \\\"temujin\\\" for Signal. Hint: <E.164|uuid:ID|group:ID|signal:group:ID|signal:+E.164>\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"message","error":"Unknown target \"temujin\" for Signal. Hint: <E.164|uuid:ID|group:ID|signal:group:ID|signal:+E.164>"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759622052}}
{"type":"message","id":"63960696","parentId":"68c3e437","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:13:56.235Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The message tool failed because it's trying to route through Signal, but temujin is an agent, not a Signal contact. According to AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md, I should be using `sessions_spawn` with `message()` to route to specialist agents via their sessions, not via Signal.\n\nLet me check the correct approach. Looking at TOOLS.md:\n- Primary Tool: `message()` — Route tasks to specialist agents\n- Follow the `kurultai-router` skill\n\nBut the message tool requires a target that's a valid Signal recipient. The agents are separate sessions, not Signal contacts.\n\nLooking more carefully at AGENTS.md:\n\"You NEVER skip the specialist. Specialists dispatch their own work to Claude Code via ACP.\"\n\nAnd the task flow:\n\"User → Kublai (classify + route) → Specialist (via message()) → Specialist dispatches to ACP → Result\"\n\nThe routing should use sessions_send or sessions_spawn to get to the specialist agents. Let me check if there are sessions for the agents.\n\nActually, looking at the context more carefully - the agents (temujin, mongke, etc.) are other agent sessions. I should use sessions_send to send a message to temujin's session.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the available sessions and route properly to temujin."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4bfe74c3e0fb4f94936f87bd","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["agent"],"limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":313,"output":284,"cacheRead":19136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19733,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772759622063}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5ae72c7","parentId":"63960696","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:13:56.324Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4bfe74c3e0fb4f94936f87bd","toolName":"sessions_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"signal\",\n      \"displayName\": \"+19194133445\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"signal\",\n        \"to\": \"+19194133445\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1772759608395,\n      \"sessionId\": \"28ee27f9-3958-466c-b6b9-e6675f181120\",\n      \"model\": \"glm-5\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 202752,\n      \"totalTokens\": 0,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"high\",\n      \"systemSent\": false,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"signal\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"+19194133445\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/28ee27f9-3958-466c-b6b9-e6675f181120.jsonl\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"count":1,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:main:main","kind":"other","channel":"signal","displayName":"+19194133445","deliveryContext":{"channel":"signal","to":"+19194133445"},"updatedAt":1772759608395,"sessionId":"28ee27f9-3958-466c-b6b9-e6675f181120","model":"glm-5","contextTokens":202752,"totalTokens":0,"thinkingLevel":"high","systemSent":false,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"signal","lastTo":"+19194133445","transcriptPath":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/28ee27f9-3958-466c-b6b9-e6675f181120.jsonl"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759636313}}
{"type":"message","id":"cddfdc22","parentId":"b5ae72c7","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:14:09.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_list only shows the main agent (Kublai). The specialist agents (temujin, mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei) don't appear as active sessions. This means either:\n1. They haven't been spawned yet\n2. They're defined differently (as separate agent workspaces, not sessions)\n\nLooking at MEMORY.md and AGENTS.md, it mentions \"6-agent Kurultai with independent workspaces\" and the agents have workspaces at `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/`.\n\nSince there's no active temujin session, I should spawn one or handle this myself. But AGENTS.md says \"NEVER execute specialist tasks yourself — ALWAYS route to the specialist agent via message()\".\n\nLooking at the kurultai-router skill that's referenced, I should read it to understand the correct routing mechanism. Let me check if the skill file exists and read it.\n\nActually, looking at the available skills list, I don't see kurultai-router listed. Let me try to read it anyway to understand the routing protocol.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The specialist agents don't have active sessions yet. Let me check the routing skill to understand how to properly route to temujin."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f7d11e3a787f4a76aa99537e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":18387,"output":282,"cacheRead":1600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20269,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772759636324}}
{"type":"message","id":"d461452a","parentId":"cddfdc22","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:14:09.189Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f7d11e3a787f4a76aa99537e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: kurultai-router\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: \"Structured task routing for the Kurultai multi-agent system\"\nmetadata:\n  openclaw:\n    category: \"coordination\"\n    agent: \"kublai\"\n---\n\n# Kurultai Router Skill\n\nYou are Kublai, Squad Lead of the Kurultai. This skill defines your routing decision tree. Follow it for EVERY inbound task.\n\n---\n\n## NEVER GATES (check BEFORE doing anything)\n\n- NEVER produce design docs, code, research, content, or analysis yourself.\n- NEVER execute a specialist task -- ALWAYS route via message().\n- NEVER write more than a brief routing acknowledgment. If you catch yourself writing task output -> STOP -> route instead.\n- NEVER hold specialist work \"until later.\" Delegate NOW.\n- NEVER spawn ACP to do work a specialist handles.\n\nIf any NEVER gate fires, STOP immediately and route.\n\n---\n\n## ROUTING DECISION TREE\n\n### STEP 1: Extract Primary Verb\n\nIdentify the first actionable verb in the task. Map it to a verb category:\n\n| Verb Category | Verbs |\n|---------------|-------|\n| BUILD | code, build, implement, fix, deploy, ship, create, design, architect, plan, spec, brainstorm, prototype, debug, refactor, migrate |\n| RESEARCH | research, investigate, discover, explore, find, study, survey, benchmark, compare |\n| WRITE | write, document, blog, draft, describe, edit, copy, content, changelog, readme |\n| ANALYZE | test, verify, validate, audit, review, analyze, check, scan, assess, evaluate, profile |\n| OPERATE | monitor, alert, restart, backup, restore, health, uptime, incident, failover, watch, track |\n| COORDINATE | triage, prioritize, coordinate, synthesize, plan (system-wide), assess (agent), status |\n\n### STEP 2: Map Verb Category to Agent\n\n| Verb Category | Agent | Domain |\n|---------------|-------|--------|\n| BUILD | temujin | Code, builds, bugs, APIs, deploy, design, architecture, payment, protocol, SDK |\n| RESEARCH | mongke | Market research, competitor analysis, fact-finding, ecosystem discovery |\n| WRITE | chagatai | Blog posts, documentation, marketing copy, changelogs, creative writing |\n| ANALYZE | jochi | Testing, security audits, code review, error investigation, data analysis, pattern recognition |\n| OPERATE | ogedei | Monitoring, alerting, restarts, backups, uptime, health checks, incident response |\n| COORDINATE | kublai | Triage decisions, cross-agent coordination, system-wide assessment, routing review |\n\n### STEP 3: Apply Disambiguation Rules (first-match-wins)\n\n**CRITICAL:** When a task contains BOTH a research verb AND a domain-specific noun (payment, protocol, x402, design, security), the domain noun wins. Research is secondary when paired with an implementation or security domain. Apply these rules BEFORE defaulting to the verb-category mapping:\n\nIf the task matches multiple verb categories, apply these rules in order:\n\n| # | If task contains... | Route to | Reason |\n|---|---------------------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | research + security/vulnerability/audit/safety/prompt injection | jochi | Security analysis, not market research |\n| 2 | design/architect/plan/brainstorm + research | temujin | Design tasks, research is secondary |\n| 3 | payment/billing/pricing/x402/protocol/SDK + research | temujin | Implementation domain |\n| 4 | build/implement + infrastructure | temujin | Building infra = code |\n| 5 | monitor + infrastructure | ogedei | Monitoring infra = ops |\n| 6 | fix + cron/backup/monitor | ogedei | Fixing ops tooling = ops |\n| 7 | write + test | jochi | Writing tests = analysis |\n| 8 | document + api | chagatai | API docs = content |\n| 9 | marketing + copy/content | chagatai | Marketing = content |\n| 10 | validate/validation + deploy/deployment | jochi | Deployment validation = analysis |\n| 11 | investigate + error/failure/spike | jochi | Error investigation = analysis, NOT ops |\n| 12 | fix + code/script/bug | temujin | Code fixes = development, NOT ops |\n| 13 | Kurultai architecture/OpenClaw design/agent system design | kublai | System architecture ownership |\n\n### STEP 4: Self-Routing Prevention\n\nBefore finalizing, check for self-routing traps:\n\n- If task says \"triage stalled agent: X\" and destination = X -> redirect to jochi (or kublai if X is jochi)\n- If task says \"assessment\" and mentions agent X and destination = X -> redirect to jochi\n- If task says \"tock assessment\" and destination = kublai -> redirect to jochi\n- NEVER route a triage/investigation task to the agent being investigated\n\n### STEP 5: Detect Skill Hint\n\nBased on destination and task content, attach the best skill hint:\n\n| Agent | Task Content | Skill Hint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| temujin | design, architect, brainstorm, plan, protocol, payment | /horde-brainstorming |\n| temujin | debug, failing, broken, error, crash | /systematic-debugging |\n| temujin | deploy, railway, production | /dev-deploy |\n| mongke | scrape, extract, crawl | /scrapling-research |\n| mongke | research, investigate, discover, explore | /horde-learn |\n| chagatai | blog, article, long-form, content | /content-research-writer |\n| chagatai | changelog, release notes | /changelog-generator |\n| jochi | debug, bug, failure, error, crash | /systematic-debugging |\n| jochi | review, audit, security | /code-reviewer |\n| ogedei | health, diagnostic, system check | /kurultai-health |\n| ogedei | deploy, railway, production | /dev-deploy |\n\n### STEP 6: Construct message()\n\nRoute via message() with this structure:\n\n```\nmessage({\n  to: \"<agent_name>\",\n  text: \"TASK: <what to do>\\nSKILL: <skill_hint or omit>\\nCONTEXT: <background and why>\\nURGENCY: high|normal|low\\nSUCCESS: <how to verify completion>\"\n})\n```\n\n### STEP 7: Log to Task Ledger\n\nAfter routing, log the decision:\n\n```\nexec(\"python3 -c \\\"import json,os; os.makedirs('/Users/kublai/.openclaw/tasks',exist_ok=True); open('/Users/kublai/.openclaw/tasks/task-ledger.jsonl','a').write(json.dumps({'event':'ROUTED','agent':'<agent>','task_summary':'<first 100 chars>','method':'skill','ts':__import__('datetime').datetime.now().isoformat()})+chr(10))\\\"\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## MULTI-DOMAIN TASK DECOMPOSITION\n\nIf a task spans multiple domains:\n\n1. Identify the distinct domain components\n2. Route each component to the appropriate specialist via separate message() calls\n3. Note dependencies between components in each message\n4. Track the multi-part task for synthesis when all parts complete\n\nExample: \"Research competitors and build a pricing page\"\n- message() to mongke: \"TASK: Research competitor pricing models...\"\n- message() to temujin: \"TASK: Build pricing page (pending mongke's research)...\"\n\n---\n\n## ROUTING EXAMPLES\n\n### Example 1: Code Task\n**Input:** \"Build a login feature with OAuth\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"build\" -> BUILD\n- Step 2: BUILD -> temujin\n- Step 3: No disambiguation needed\n- Step 5: No skill hint match\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"temujin\", text: \"TASK: Build login feature with OAuth\\nCONTEXT: New auth system\\nURGENCY: normal\\nSUCCESS: OAuth login working end-to-end\" })`\n\n### Example 2: Security Research\n**Input:** \"Research prompt injection vulnerabilities in our API\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"research\" -> RESEARCH\n- Step 2: RESEARCH -> mongke\n- Step 3: Rule #1 fires: research + security -> jochi\n- Step 5: Skill hint: /code-reviewer\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"jochi\", text: \"TASK: Research prompt injection vulnerabilities in our API\\nSKILL: /code-reviewer\\nURGENCY: high\\nSUCCESS: Vulnerability report with remediation steps\" })`\n\n### Example 3: Design Task with Research\n**Input:** \"Research payment protocols and design an x402 integration\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"research\" -> RESEARCH\n- Step 2: RESEARCH -> mongke\n- Step 3: Rule #3 fires: payment + protocol + research -> temujin\n- Step 5: Skill hint: /horde-brainstorming\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"temujin\", text: \"TASK: Design x402 payment protocol integration\\nSKILL: /horde-brainstorming\\nCONTEXT: Research existing payment protocols as part of design\\nURGENCY: normal\\nSUCCESS: Architecture doc + working prototype\" })`\n\n### Example 4: Stalled Agent Triage\n**Input:** \"Triage stalled agent: jochi has 5 queued tasks with 0 completions\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"triage\" -> COORDINATE\n- Step 2: COORDINATE -> kublai\n- Step 4: Self-routing prevention: task mentions jochi, but destination is kublai (safe). However, this is a triage task -- redirect to jochi... but jochi IS the stalled agent -> redirect to kublai. Final: kublai.\n\n### Example 5: Multi-Domain\n**Input:** \"Write a blog post about our new API endpoint and deploy it\"\n- Decompose: write blog (chagatai) + deploy (temujin/ogedei)\n- message() to chagatai: \"TASK: Write blog post about the new API endpoint...\"\n- message() to temujin: \"TASK: Deploy the blog post to production...\"\n\n### Example 6: Ops Fix\n**Input:** \"Fix the backup cron job that's been failing\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"fix\" -> BUILD\n- Step 2: BUILD -> temujin\n- Step 3: Rule #6 fires: fix + cron/backup -> ogedei\n- Step 5: Skill hint: /kurultai-health\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"ogedei\", text: \"TASK: Fix failing backup cron job\\nSKILL: /kurultai-health\\nURGENCY: high\\nSUCCESS: Cron job runs successfully\" })`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759649178}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d7550db","parentId":"d461452a","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:14:44.825Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the routing protocol. The message() function is the correct tool, but I need to use it correctly. The SKILL.md shows:\n\n```\nmessage({\n  to: \"<agent_name>\",\n  text: \"TASK: <what to do>\\nSKILL: <skill_hint or omit>\\nCONTEXT: <background and why>\\nURGENCY: high|normal|low\\nSUCCESS: <how to verify completion>\"\n})\n```\n\nBut my earlier attempt with `target: \"temujin\"` failed because it tried to route through Signal. Let me look at the message tool schema again to see the correct parameter name for agent routing.\n\nLooking at the tool definition:\n- `target` is for \"Target channel/user id or name\"\n- `channel` is for specifying the channel type\n\nFor agent routing, I might need a different approach. Looking at the sessions_list result, there's only the main session. The agent workspaces exist at `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/`, but there are no active sessions for them.\n\nThis suggests the agents are defined as separate agent instances in OpenClaw, but they're not running as sessions. The message tool with a target of \"temujin\" should work if temujin is configured as a valid recipient.\n\nWait - looking at the error: \"Unknown target \\\"temujin\\\" for Signal.\" This suggests the message tool is trying to route through Signal specifically. But agents should be internal to OpenClaw.\n\nLet me check if there's a different way to address agents. The schema shows `channel` parameter which defaults to the current channel (Signal in this case). Maybe I need to omit the channel or use a different value.\n\nActually, looking at AGENTS.md again:\n\"### Primary Tool: `message()` — Route tasks to specialist agents\nFollow the `kurultai-router` skill (`~/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md`) for all routing decisions. Specialist tasks go to agents via message(), not ACP.\"\n\nAnd looking at the message tool schema more carefully, there's a note about `targets` for multiple recipients. But the key issue is that `target` is being interpreted as a Signal recipient.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Maybe the agents are configured as OpenClaw agents and I need to use a specific format for the target. Let me check if the agents are defined in OpenClaw config.\n\nActually, I should try using the message tool with just the agent name as the target without the Signal context. Let me also try using sessions_send since that's for sending to sessions.\n\nWait - sessions_send requires a sessionKey or label. The agents might have predefined labels. Let me try using sessions_send with \"temujin\" as the label.\n\nActually, looking at the kurultai-router skill more carefully, it says to use message() with the agent name as the `to` parameter. But in my tool schema, the parameter is `target`, not `to`. This could be a schema mismatch.\n\nLet me try message() with the target parameter and see if I can specify it differently. Maybe I need to use the channel parameter to indicate it's an internal agent message rather than Signal.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that the agents are not configured as Signal contacts - they're OpenClaw agents that need to be contacted internally. Let me try sessions_spawn to spawn temujin or check if there's a way to send to agents directly.\n\nHmm, looking at TOOLS.md again:\n\"### Primary Tool: `message()` — Route tasks to specialist agents\"\n\nBut the message tool seems to be for external messaging (Signal, Telegram, etc.). For internal agent routing, maybe I need to spawn the agent first using sessions_spawn with a specific agentId.\n\nLet me check agents_list to see what agents are available:","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The kurultai-router skill is clear: I should route to temujin since this is about payment implementation. Let me check available agents and route properly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6696f4b97a3941ff93f04c42","name":"agents_list","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2680,"output":830,"cacheRead":19968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23478,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772759649190}}
