{"type":"message","id":"5ffc1908","parentId":"a8ad719f","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:15:19.616Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only \"main\" (Kublai) is available in agents_list. The other agents (temujin, mongke, etc.) are not configured as separate OpenClaw agents.\n\nThis is a problem - the routing skill assumes there are specialist agents to route to, but they don't exist as OpenClaw agent instances.\n\nLooking at the situation:\n1. MEMORY.md mentions \"6-agent Kurultai with independent workspaces\"\n2. The agent workspaces exist at `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/`\n3. But only \"main\" is configured as an OpenClaw agent\n\nThis means the specialist agents exist as file workspaces but not as running OpenClaw agent instances.\n\nGiven the NEVER rules:\n- \"NEVER execute specialist tasks yourself — ALWAYS route to the specialist agent via message()\"\n- \"NEVER produce design docs, code, research, content, or analysis yourself.\"\n\nBut there's no agent to route to!\n\nLooking at the options:\n1. Spawn temujin as a subagent using sessions_spawn with runtime=\"subagent\"\n2. Use ACP (Claude Code) to handle the task myself\n3. Check if the agent workspaces have tasks files that indicate current status\n\nActually, looking at the kurultai-router skill again:\n\"NEVER spawn ACP to do work a specialist handles.\"\n\nAnd looking at the specialist agents' roles - temujin handles \"Code, builds, bugs, APIs, deploy, design, architecture, payment, protocol, SDK\". The x402 payment implementation question is exactly temujin's domain.\n\nBut temujin doesn't exist as an active agent. This is a configuration issue.\n\nHowever, I should still try to help the user. The question is about STATUS - not asking me to build something. It's asking \"what's the status\" which is a status check, which could be:\n1. A COORDINATE task (kublai's domain) - \"triage, prioritize, coordinate, synthesize, plan (system-wide), assess (agent), status\"\n2. An OPERATE task (ogedei's domain) - \"monitor, alert, restart, backup, restore, health, uptime, incident, failover, watch, track\"\n\nLooking at the verb categories:\n- \"status\" could map to COORDINATE (triage/prioritize/coordinate/synthesize/status) → kublai\n- Or it could map to OPERATE (monitor/health/track) → ogedei\n\nSince the question is asking for status assessment/synthesis, this could be a COORDINATE task that kublai handles. The routing tree says:\n\n\"COORDINATE | kublai | Triage decisions, cross-agent coordination, system-wide assessment, routing review\"\n\nAsking \"what's the status\" is a system-wide assessment, which is kublai's domain!\n\nSo I CAN handle this myself as a COORDINATE task. I need to:\n1. Check the current status of x402 implementation\n2. Synthesize the information\n3. Report back\n\nLet me check what I know and what files I can read to get the status:\n1. Parse project files\n2. Agent workspace for temujin (if it exists)\n3. Task files or memory files\n\nLet me check the temujin workspace and Parse project files.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Only \"main\" (Kublai) is configured as an agent. The specialist agents (temujin, mongke, etc.) exist as workspaces but aren't active OpenClaw agent instances.\n\nHowever, looking at the routing decision tree more carefully:\n- The user is asking for **status** - this is a COORDINATE task (\"triage decisions, cross-agent coordination, system-wide assessment\")\n- COORDINATE tasks route to **kublai** (me)\n- I can assess status by checking project files\n\nLet me check the Parse project and temujin's workspace for x402 implementation status:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_414422b14e41451db9aeebb7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5f4f4e82727a4cedb5045a97","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/tasks/queued.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d509918e62364d5a91b1ee10","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin -name \"*.md\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":4138,"output":919,"cacheRead":19392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772759684850}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf32ffd3","parentId":"5ffc1908","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:15:19.642Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_414422b14e41451db9aeebb7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Temüjin — Long-Term Memory\n\n**Role:** Development Specialist  \n**Model:** bailian/MiniMax-M2.5\n\n---\n\n## Core Identity\n\n- **Mission:** Build systems that work\n- **Focus:** Code generation, infrastructure, deployment\n- **Operating Principle:** Spec-first, TDD, quality gates\n\n---\n\n## Key Learnings\n\n### Development Practices\n- Spec-first development (write spec before code)\n- Test-driven development (tests before implementation)\n- Quality gates (lint, tests, type check before deploy)\n- Inner retry loop (auto-fix common failures)\n\n### What Works\n- Subagent spawning for parallel development\n- Railway for deployment\n- TypeScript for type safety\n- Next.js for full-stack apps\n\n### What Doesn't Work\n- Deploying without tests\n- Manual deployment processes\n- Ignoring TypeScript errors\n\n---\n\n## Active Tasks\n\n1. **Parse Agent Services** — Prompt injection + ad detector + x402\n   - Status: Code complete, TypeScript errors blocking deploy\n   - Next: Fix errors, redeploy\n\n2. **Heartbeat Master Daemon** — Continuous operation\n   - Status: ✅ RUNNING\n   - Next: Monitor for 24h\n\n---\n\n## Heartbeat Tasks\n\n- deployment_monitor: Every 30 minutes\n- code_quality: Every 120 minutes\n\n---\n\n*Last updated: 2026-03-01*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759719632}}
