{"type":"message","id":"b128737d","parentId":"2c4a0845","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:16:24.307Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1a6dcbb034c444f1916069a7","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/SPEC-parse-for-agents.md:In addition to subscription, users pay per-evaluation costs that cover:\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/SPEC-parse-for-agents.md:| DoS via large payloads | Request size limits (1MB body), test case limits per tier |\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/ARCHITECTURE.md:| PAY_PER_USE | 2 | Pay-per-analysis users |\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/ARCHITECTURE.md:type QueueType = \"PRO_SUBSCRIPTION\" | \"PAY_PER_USE\" | \"FREE_TIER\";\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/d3-format/README.md:Yet rounding error is not the only reason to customize number formatting. A table of numbers should be formatted consistently for comparison; above, 0.0 would be better than 0. Large numbers should have grouped digits (e.g., 42,000) or be in scientific or metric notation (4.2e+4, 42k). Currencies should have fixed precision ($3.50). Reported numerical results should be rounded to significant digits (4021 becomes 4000). Number formats should appropriate to the reader’s locale (42.000,00 or 42,000.00). The list goes on.\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/schemas.ts:function handleObjectResult(result: ParsePayload, final: ParsePayload, key: PropertyKey) {\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/schemas.ts:function handleOptionalObjectResult(result: ParsePayload, final: ParsePayload, key: PropertyKey, input: any) {\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/schemas.ts:          payload.value[keyResult.value as PropertyKey] = keyResult.value;\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/schemas.ts:              payload.value[keyResult.value as PropertyKey] = result.value;\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/schemas.ts:          payload.value[keyResult.value as PropertyKey] = result.value;\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/checks.ts:    payload.issues.push(...util.prefixIssues(property, result.issues));\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/checks.ts:          value: (payload.value as any)[def.property],\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/checks.ts:        return result.then((result) => handleCheckPropertyResult(result, payload, def.property));\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/checks.ts:      handleCheckPropertyResult(result, payload, def.property);\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/core/util.ts:  float32: [-3.4028234663852886e38, 3.4028234663852886e38],\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/mini/tests/number.test.ts:  // -3.4028234663852886e38, 3.4028234663852886e38;\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/mini/tests/number.test.ts:  expect(() => z.parse(a, 3.4028234663852886e38 * 2)).toThrow(); // Exceeds max\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/mini/tests/number.test.ts:  expect(() => z.parse(a, -3.4028234663852886e38 * 2)).toThrow(); // Exceeds min\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/classic/tests/to-json-schema.test.ts:        \"maximum\": 3.4028234663852886e+38,\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/zod/src/v4/classic/tests/to-json-schema.test.ts:        \"minimum\": -3.4028234663852886e+38,\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/which-boxed-primitive/CHANGELOG.md:- [Dev Deps] update `eslint`, `@ljharb/eslint-config`, `tape` [`f8a0afe`](https://github.com/inspect-js/which-boxed-primitive/commit/f8a0afea82938d64f3d2d240268afbd346d0c4da)\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/node_modules/tldts/src/data/trie.ts:const rules: ITrie = [0,{\"ac\":[1,{\"com\":_2