{"type":"message","id":"6b99bb48","parentId":"b128737d","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:16:36.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The grep results show there's an x402.ts file at `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/x402.ts` - this is interesting! It's in a separate `parse-for-agents` directory, not the main `parse-github` directory.\n\nThe main parse-github SPEC file mentions \"pay per-evaluation costs\" but doesn't specifically mention x402.\n\nLet me read the x402.ts file and also look for more x402-related content in the Parse project. I should also check the PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md spec file.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I found an x402.ts file at `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/x402.ts`. Let me read this file and the spec files to get the complete picture:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_baf251522f4640278e87166b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/x402.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_46c1873eff404f63b5081f99","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_af1850d1bb504343b16673f6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/SPEC-parse-for-agents.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":93081,"output":235,"cacheRead":4352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97668,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772759784308}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab35e766","parentId":"6b99bb48","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:16:36.604Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_baf251522f4640278e87166b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { paymentMiddleware, x402ResourceServer } from \"@x402/hono\";\nimport { ExactEvmScheme } from \"@x402/evm/exact/server\";\nimport { HTTPFacilitatorClient } from \"@x402/core/server\";\nimport type { Context, Next } from \"hono\";\n\nconst X402_ENABLED = process.env.X402_ENABLED === \"true\";\nconst WALLET = process.env.X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS || \"\";\nconst NETWORK = (process.env.X402_NETWORK || \"eip155:8453\") as `${string}:${string}`;\nconst FACILITATOR_URL = process.env.X402_FACILITATOR_URL || \"https://facilitator.x402.org\";\n\n// Pricing table (USDC on Base L2)\nexport const PRICING = {\n  analyze: { quick: \"$0.01\", standard: \"$0.05\", deep: \"$0.15\" },\n  evaluate: \"$0.01\",\n  chat: \"$0.005\",\n} as const;\n\n// Initialize x402 middleware only when enabled and wallet configured\nlet x402MW: ((c: Context, next: Next) => Promise<Response | void>) | null = null;\n\nif (X402_ENABLED && WALLET) {\n  const facilitatorClient = new HTTPFacilitatorClient({ url: FACILITATOR_URL });\n  const resourceServer = new x402ResourceServer(facilitatorClient)\n    .register(NETWORK, new ExactEvmScheme());\n\n  x402MW = paymentMiddleware(\n    {\n      \"POST /v1/analyze\": {\n        accepts: {\n          scheme: \"exact\",\n          price: PRICING.analyze.standard,\n          network: NETWORK,\n          payTo: WALLET,\n        },\n        description: \"Media credibility analysis\",\n      },\n      \"POST /v1/evaluate\": {\n        accepts: {\n          scheme: \"exact\",\n          price: PRICING.evaluate,\n          network: NETWORK,\n          payTo: WALLET,\n        },\n        description: \"Prompt safety and quality evaluation\",\n      },\n      \"POST /v1/chat\": {\n        accepts: {\n          scheme: \"exact\",\n          price: PRICING.chat,\n          network: NETWORK,\n          payTo: WALLET,\n        },\n        description: \"Chat with Parse AI assistant\",\n      },\n    },\n    resourceServer,\n  );\n\n  console.log(`[x402] Payment middleware enabled — wallet: ${WALLET.slice(0, 6)}...${WALLET.slice(-4)}, network: ${NETWORK}`);\n} else if (X402_ENABLED && !WALLET) {\n  console.warn(\"[x402] X402_ENABLED=true but X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS not set — payments disabled\");\n}\n\n/**\n * Middleware that intercepts x402 payment headers on POST routes.\n * If payment header present → verifies via x402 SDK → sets x402Paid flag → proceeds.\n * If no payment header → passes through to normal API key auth.\n */\nexport function x402Guard() {\n  return async (c: Context, next: Next) => {\n    // Only handle POST requests with payment headers when x402 is active\n    if (c.req.method !== \"POST\" || !x402MW) {\n      await next();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Check for x402 payment header (protocol uses \"x-payment\")\n    const hasPayment = c.req.header(\"x-payment\");\n    if (hasPayment) {\n      // Route through x402 middleware for verification + settlement\n      return x402MW(c, async () => {\n        // Payment verified — mark context so auth middleware skips API key check\n        c.set(\"x402Paid\", true);\n        await next();\n      });\n    }\n\n    // No payment header — fall through to API key auth\n    await next();\n  };\n}\n\nexport function isX402Enabled(): boolean {\n  return X402_ENABLED && !!WALLET;\n}\n\nexport function getPricingInfo() {\n  return {\n    enabled: isX402Enabled(),\n    currency: \"USDC\",\n    network: NETWORK,\n    payTo: WALLET || \"not_configured\",\n    facilitator: FACILITATOR_URL,\n    endpoints: {\n      \"POST /v1/analyze\": PRICING.analyze,\n      \"POST /v1/evaluate\": PRICING.evaluate,\n      \"POST /v1/chat\": PRICING.chat,\n    },\n    free_endpoints: [\"GET /v1/models\", \"GET /v1/pricing\", \"POST /v1/keys/generate\"],\n    free_tier: {\n      description: \"Generate an API key for limited free access\",\n      url: \"/v1/keys/generate\",\n    },\n    agent_integration: {\n      typescript: 'npm install @x402/fetch — then use wrapFetch(fetch, walletClient)',\n      python: 'pip install x402 — then use wrap_requests(session, wallet)',\n      cli: 'npm install -g @x402/purl — then use purl POST <url>',\n    },\n  };\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759796594}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bd9250c","parentId":"ab35e766","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:16:36.623Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_46c1873eff404f63b5081f99","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Parse for Agents — Implementation Plan\n\n*Created: March 5, 2026*\n*Goal: $1,500 MRR by Day 90*\n\n---\n\n## 1. Product Vision\n\n**Parse for Agents** is an API service that lets AI developers test, evaluate, and benchmark prompts in isolated sandbox environments. One API call = sandboxed execution + structured evaluation + scored results.\n\n**Tagline**: \"CI/CD for your prompts.\"\n\n### Why This Wins\n\nThe market has eval frameworks (PromptFoo, Braintrust, LangSmith) and sandbox runtimes (E2B, Modal). Nobody combines them. Parse already has:\n- Multi-LLM orchestration (4 providers, fallback chain)\n- BullMQ queue infrastructure\n- Credit/billing system with Stripe\n- API key management with scopes\n- Webhook delivery system\n\nWe're not starting from scratch — we're extending a production system.\n\n### Target Users\n1. **Agent builders** — Need to regression-test prompts before deploying agents\n2. **Prompt engineers** — Want structured evaluation beyond \"does it work?\"\n3. **AI startups** — Need automated prompt QA in CI/CD pipelines\n4. **Enterprise teams** — Compliance requirement to audit LLM outputs before production\n\n---\n\n## 2. Competitive Positioning\n\n| Competitor | What They Do | Gap |\n|-----------|-------------|-----|\n| **PromptFoo** | Local eval framework, YAML configs | No sandboxing, no hosted API, steep learning curve |\n| **Braintrust** | Logging + evals + datasets | Enterprise-priced ($500+/mo), no sandbox |\n| **LangSmith** | LangChain observability + evals | Tied to LangChain ecosystem |\n| **HumanLoop** | Prompt management + evals | No code execution, no sandbox |\n| **E2B** | Sandboxed code execution | No eval framework, just raw sandboxes |\n| **Arize Phoenix** | Tracing + evals | Post-hoc observability, not pre-deployment testing |\n\n### Our Niche\n**\"Sandboxed prompt evaluation as a service\"** — The missing middle between eval frameworks and sandbox runtimes. Ship a prompt test in one API call, get structured scores back.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Core API Design\n\n### Base URL\n```\nhttps://api.parse.news/v1/agents\n```\n\n### Authentication\nReuse existing Parse API key system (`parse_pk_prod_*` / `parse_pk_dev_*`). Add new scopes:\n- `prompt_test` — Run single prompt tests\n- `prompt_eval` — Run evaluation suites\n- `sandbox_exec` — Execute code in sandbox\n- `datasets` — Manage test datasets\n\n### Endpoints\n\n#### 3.1 Prompt Test (Core)\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/test\n```\nRun a single prompt against one or more LLM providers with structured evaluation.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": {\n    \"system\": \"You are a helpful assistant...\",\n    \"user\": \"Explain quantum computing in 3 sentences.\",\n    \"variables\": { \"topic\": \"quantum computing\", \"length\": 3 }\n  },\n  \"providers\": [\"deepseek-v3\", \"gpt-4o\", \"claude-sonnet\"],\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"relevance\", \"accuracy\", \"conciseness\", \"safety\"],\n    \"rubric\": \"Score 1-5 on each criterion\",\n    \"assertions\": [\n      { \"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\" },\n      { \"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200 },\n      { \"type\": \"no_hallucination\", \"context\": \"...\" },\n      { \"type\": \"json_schema\", \"schema\": { ... } }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"sandbox\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"timeout_ms\": 30000,\n    \"memory_mb\": 256,\n    \"network\": false\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 500,\n    \"runs\": 3\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"test_abc123\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"duration_ms\": 4520,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"deepseek-v3\",\n      \"runs\": [\n        {\n          \"output\": \"Quantum computing uses qubits...\",\n          \"tokens\": { \"input\": 45, \"output\": 82 },\n          \"latency_ms\": 1200,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n          \"eval\": {\n            \"scores\": {\n              \"relevance\": 4.5,\n              \"accuracy\": 4.0,\n              \"conciseness\": 5.0,\n              \"safety\": 5.0\n            },\n            \"overall\": 4.6,\n            \"assertions\": [\n              { \"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\", \"passed\": true },\n              { \"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200, \"passed\": true }\n            ],\n            \"pass\": true\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"aggregate\": {\n        \"avg_score\": 4.6,\n        \"avg_latency_ms\": 1180,\n        \"avg_cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n        \"pass_rate\": 1.0\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"comparison\": {\n    \"best_provider\": \"deepseek-v3\",\n    \"best_score\": 4.6,\n    \"cost_efficiency\": { \"deepseek-v3\": 15333, \"gpt-4o\": 230, \"claude-sonnet\": 460 }\n  },\n  \"credits_used\": 3\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2 Evaluation Suite\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/eval\n```\nRun a prompt against a dataset of test cases.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": {\n    \"system\": \"Extract the sentiment...\",\n    \"user_template\": \"Analyze: {{text}}\"\n  },\n  \"dataset\": \"ds_sentiment_v2\",\n  \"providers\": [\"deepseek-v3\"],\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"accuracy\"],\n    \"ground_truth_field\": \"expected_sentiment\"\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"concurrency\": 5,\n    \"webhook_url\": \"https://your-app.com/webhook\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response (async via webhook):**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_xyz789\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"dataset_size\": 100,\n  \"pass_rate\": 0.87,\n  \"results_url\": \"https://api.parse.news/v1/agents/eval/eval_xyz789/results\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"accuracy\": { \"mean\": 0.87, \"std\": 0.12, \"p50\": 0.90, \"p95\": 0.65 },\n    \"total_cost_usd\": 0.15,\n    \"total_duration_ms\": 45000\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.3 Datasets\n```\nPOST   /v1/agents/datasets              # Create dataset\nGET    /v1/agents/datasets              # List datasets\nGET    /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Get dataset\nPUT    /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Update dataset\nDELETE /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Delete dataset\nPOST   /v1/agents/datasets/:id/rows     # Add rows\n```\n\n**Dataset Row:**\n```json\n{\n  \"input\": { \"text\": \"I love this product!\" },\n  \"expected\": { \"sentiment\": \"positive\", \"confidence\": 0.95 },\n  \"tags\": [\"english\", \"product-review\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.4 Sandbox Execution\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/sandbox/run\n```\nExecute arbitrary code (Python/JS/TS) in an isolated environment for tool-use testing.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"runtime\": \"python3.12\",\n  \"code\": \"import json\\nresult = json.loads(input_data)\\nprint(result['name'])\",\n  \"input_data\": \"{\\\"name\\\": \\\"test\\\"}\",\n  \"timeout_ms\": 10000,\n  \"memory_mb\": 128,\n  \"network\": false,\n  \"packages\": [\"requests\", \"pandas\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.5 History & Comparison\n```\nGET /v1/agents/tests                    # List test runs\nGET /v1/agents/tests/:id               # Get test details\nGET /v1/agents/tests/compare?ids=a,b   # Compare two runs\nGET /v1/agents/usage                    # Usage stats\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Sandbox Isolation Architecture\n\n### Phase 1: Lightweight Isolation (Week 1-4)\nUse **Docker containers** with resource limits on Railway.\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  Parse API Server                   │\n│  POST /v1/agents/test                               │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              BullMQ \"agent-test\" Queue              │\n│  Priority: 1=Pro, 2=Pay, 3=Free                     │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              Agent Test Worker                       │\n│                                                      │\n│  1. Validate prompt + eval criteria                  │\n│  2. Call LLM provider(s) via existing llm.ts         │\n│  3. Run eval assertions (contains, schema, etc.)     │\n│  4. Score with judge LLM (DeepSeek as judge)         │\n│  5. Aggregate results                                │\n│  6. Return via webhook or polling                    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Why Docker first**: No code execution in Phase 1. We're testing *prompts*, not running arbitrary code. The LLM calls go through our existing provider chain. Isolation is at the process level via BullMQ workers.\n\n### Phase 2: Code Sandbox (Week 5-8)\nAdd E2B or Firecracker-based sandboxes for tool-use testing.\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              Agent Test Worker                       │\n│                                                      │\n│  When sandbox.enabled && code execution needed:      │\n│                                                      │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │        E2B Sandbox (or self-hosted)             │ │\n│  │  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐     │ │\n│  │  │ Python   │  │ Node.js  │  │ Custom   │     │ │\n│  │  │ 3.12     │  │ 20       │  │ Docker   │     │ │\n│  │  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────┘     │ │\n│  │                                                │ │\n│  │  Limits: 256MB RAM, 30s timeout, no network   │ │\n│  │  Cleanup: Auto-destroy after execution         │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Resource Limits by Tier\n\n| Resource | Free | Pro | Max |\n|----------|------|-----|-----|\n| Timeout | 10s | 30s | 60s |\n| Memory | 128MB | 256MB | 512MB |\n| Network | No | No | Optional |\n| Concurrency | 1 | 5 | 20 |\n| Runs/test | 1 | 5 | 10 |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Evaluation Engine\n\n### Built-in Eval Criteria\n\n| Criterion | How It Works | Method |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| **relevance** | Does output address the prompt? | LLM-as-judge (DeepSeek) |\n| **accuracy** | Factual correctness | LLM-as-judge + ground truth comparison |\n| **conciseness** | Appropriate length for task | Token count + LLM-as-judge |\n| **safety** | No harmful/biased content | Parse's existing deception + bias agents |\n| **coherence** | Logical flow and consistency | LLM-as-judge |\n| **instruction_following** | Did it follow the prompt format? | Rule-based + LLM |\n| **hallucination** | Fabricated facts not in context | RAG faithfulness check |\n| **toxicity** | Harmful language detection | Classifier |\n| **injection_safety** | Hidden instruction & prompt injection detection | Deterministic pattern matching (regex + heuristics) |\n\n### Assertion Types (Deterministic)\n\n| Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `contains` | Output contains substring |\n| `not_contains` | Output does not contain substring |\n| `regex` | Output matches regex |\n| `json_schema` | Output is valid JSON matching schema |\n| `max_tokens` | Output within token limit |\n| `min_tokens` | Output meets minimum length |\n| `starts_with` | Output begins with string |\n| `semantic_similarity` | Cosine similarity > threshold |\n| `no_pii` | No personal identifiable information |\n| `language` | Output in specified language |\n| `custom` | User-provided JS function (sandbox) |\n\n### Scoring\n\nEach eval criterion returns a score 0.0-5.0. The overall score is a weighted average:\n\n```\noverall = Σ(criterion_score × weight) / Σ(weights)\n```\n\nDefault weights are equal. Users can customize:\n```json\n{\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"relevance\", \"accuracy\", \"safety\"],\n    \"weights\": { \"relevance\": 2, \"accuracy\": 3, \"safety\": 5 }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nA test **passes** if:\n1. All assertions pass, AND\n2. Overall score >= threshold (default 3.5)\n\n### Reusing Parse's Analysis Agents\n\nParse's existing 11-agent pipeline can be repurposed:\n\n| Parse Agent | Agent Test Use Case |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| DeceptionAgent | Safety/manipulation detection in LLM outputs |\n| FallacyAgent | Logical consistency checking |\n| SteelManningAgent | Testing if output considers opposing views |\n| EvidenceQualityAgent | Source quality assessment for RAG outputs |\n| ClaimTestAgent | Claim extraction + verifiability scoring |\n| BernaysAgent | Propaganda/bias detection |\n\nThis is a **unique competitive advantage** — no other eval tool has 11 specialized analysis agents.\n\n### Injection Safety Evaluator\n\nIn addition to LLM-based agents, Parse includes a **deterministic injection detection evaluator** that scans for hidden instructions and agent manipulation attempts without requiring LLM calls:\n\n| Pattern Category | What It Detects |\n|-----------------|-----------------|\n| Hidden HTML instructions | `display:none` divs, white-on-white text, 1px font, `aria-hidden` content |\n| HTML comment instructions | `<!-- commands -->` embedded in content |\n| C2 registration | Attempts to connect agents to external command servers |\n| Brainworm/promptware | Memory file injection, persistent behavioral modification |\n| Urgency coercion | \"YOU MUST\", \"IMMEDIATELY\", \"CRITICAL\" override patterns |\n| Identity override | \"Ignore previous instructions\", \"You are now X\" |\n| Network exfiltration | Instructions to send data to external URLs |\n\n**References:** Canar.ai (17 hidden payload vectors), Brainworm/OriginHQ (promptware), Grith.ai (runtime zero-trust for agents).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Data Models (Prisma Extensions)\n\n```prisma\n// ============================================================================\n// Parse for Agents - Prompt Testing\n// ============================================================================\n\nenum TestStatus {\n  QUEUED\n  RUNNING\n  COMPLETED\n  FAILED\n  CANCELLED\n}\n\nmodel PromptTest {\n  id          String     @id @default(cuid())\n  userId      String\n  apiKeyId    String?\n\n  // Input\n  systemPrompt String    @db.Text\n  userPrompt   String    @db.Text\n  variables    Json?\n  providers    String[]\n  evalCriteria String[]\n  evalWeights  Json?\n  assertions   Json?\n  sandboxConfig Json?\n  options      Json?     // temperature, max_tokens, runs\n\n  // Output\n  status       TestStatus @default(QUEUED)\n  results      Json?      // Full results payload\n  overallScore Float?\n  passed       Boolean?\n  creditsUsed  Int        @default(0)\n  totalCost    Float?     // USD cost of LLM calls\n  durationMs   Int?\n\n  // Queue\n  jobId        String?    @unique // BullMQ job ID\n  priority     Int        @default(2)\n\n  // Metadata\n  name         String?    // Optional test name\n  tags         String[]\n  suiteId      String?    // Part of an eval suite\n\n  createdAt    DateTime   @default(now())\n  updatedAt    DateTime   @updatedAt\n\n  user         User       @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])\n  suite        EvalSuite? @relation(fields: [suiteId], references: [id])\n\n  @@index([userId, createdAt])\n  @@index([status])\n  @@index([suiteId])\n  @@index([tags])\n  @@map(\"prompt_tests\")\n}\n\nmodel EvalSuite {\n  id          String     @id @default(cuid())\n  userId      String\n  apiKeyId    String?\n\n  // Config\n  name         String\n  description  String?\n  promptTemplate Json   // { system, user_template }\n  providers    String[]\n  evalCriteria String[]\n  evalWeights  Json?\n  assertions   Json?\n\n  // Dataset\n  datasetId    String\n\n  // Results\n  status       TestStatus @default(QUEUED)\n  passRate     Float?\n  summary      Json?\n  creditsUsed  Int        @default(0)\n  totalCost    Float?\n\n  // Queue\n  jobId        String?    @unique\n  concurrency  Int        @default(3)\n  webhookUrl   String?\n\n  createdAt    DateTime   @default(now())\n  updatedAt    DateTime   @updatedAt\n\n  user         User       @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])\n  dataset      Dataset    @relation(fields: [datasetId], references: [id])\n  tests        PromptTest[]\n\n  @@index([userId, createdAt])\n  @@index([status])\n  @@map(\"eval_suites\")\n}\n\nmodel Dataset {\n  id          String     @id @default(cuid())\n  userId      String\n  name        String\n  description String?\n  rowCount    Int        @default(0)\n  schema      Json?      // Column definitions\n  tags        String[]\n\n  createdAt   DateTime   @default(now())\n  updatedAt   DateTime   @updatedAt\n\n  user        User       @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])\n  rows        DatasetRow[]\n  suites      EvalSuite[]\n\n  @@unique([userId, name])\n  @@index([userId])\n  @@map(\"datasets\")\n}\n\nmodel DatasetRow {\n  id          String     @id @default(cuid())\n  datasetId   String\n  input       Json       // Template variables\n  expected    Json?      // Ground truth\n  tags        String[]\n  rowIndex    Int        // Order within dataset\n\n  createdAt   DateTime   @default(now())\n\n  dataset     Dataset    @relation(fields: [datasetId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)\n\n  @@index([datasetId, rowIndex])\n  @@map(\"dataset_rows\")\n}\n```\n\n### New API Key Scopes\n\nAdd to existing `KeyScope` enum:\n```prisma\nenum KeyScope {\n  // ... existing scopes\n  prompt_test\n  prompt_eval\n  sandbox_exec\n  datasets\n}\n```\n\n### New Webhook Events\n\nAdd to existing `WebhookEvent` enum:\n```prisma\nenum WebhookEvent {\n  // ... existing events\n  PROMPT_TEST_COMPLETED\n  PROMPT_TEST_FAILED\n  EVAL_SUITE_COMPLETED\n  EVAL_SUITE_FAILED\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Tech Stack Decisions\n\n| Component | Choice | Rationale |\n|-----------|--------|-----------|\n| **API Framework** | Next.js API routes (existing) | Already deployed, handles auth/billing |\n| **Queue** | BullMQ (existing) | New \"agent-test\" queue alongside \"analysis\" queue |\n| **LLM Providers** | DeepSeek/MiniMax/Moonshot (existing) | Already integrated with fallback chain |\n| **Judge LLM** | DeepSeek V3.2 with thinking | Best cost/quality ratio for eval |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL + Prisma (existing) | Add new models to existing schema |\n| **Sandbox (Phase 2)** | E2B Cloud | Managed Firecracker VMs, $0.06/hr, great DX |\n| **Caching** | Redis (existing) | LLM cache already built |\n| **Docs** | Mintlify or readme.io | API documentation |\n| **SDK** | TypeScript + Python | Primary languages of target users |\n\n### Why NOT Build a Separate Service\n\nParse for Agents should be **a feature of Parse**, not a separate codebase:\n1. Shares auth, billing, webhooks, API keys — no duplication\n2. Shares LLM provider chain — cost savings\n3. Same Railway deployment — simpler ops\n4. Shared user base — cross-sell from media analysis to prompt testing\n5. Single Stripe integration — one billing system\n\n---\n\n## 8. Monetization\n\n### Pricing Tiers\n\n| Tier | Price | Credits/mo | Tests/mo | Eval Rows | Sandbox | Support |\n|------|-------|-----------|----------|-----------|---------|---------|\n| **Free** | $0 | 50 | 50 | 500 | No | Community |\n| **Pro** | $29/mo | 500 | 500 | 5,000 | Yes (10s) | Email |\n| **Team** | $99/mo | 2,000 | 2,000 | 25,000 | Yes (30s) | Priority |\n| **Enterprise** | Custom | Unlimited | Unlimited | Unlimited | Yes (60s) | Dedicated |\n\n### Credit Costs\n\n| Action | Credits |\n|--------|---------|\n| Single prompt test (1 provider, 1 run) | 1 |\n| Additional provider per test | +1 |\n| Additional run per test | +0.5 |\n| Eval suite row | 0.5 |\n| Sandbox execution | 2 |\n| Parse analysis agents (safety/bias) | 3 |\n\n### Revenue Projections\n\n**Path to $1,500 MRR by Day 90:**\n\n| Month | Free Users | Pro | Team | MRR |\n|-------|-----------|-----|------|-----|\n| 1 | 50 | 5 | 0 | $145 |\n| 2 | 200 | 20 | 3 | $877 |\n| 3 | 500 | 35 | 8 | $1,807 |\n\n**Key assumptions:**\n- Free-to-Pro conversion: 10%\n- Pro-to-Team upgrade: 15% over 3 months\n- Churn: 5%/mo\n- CAC: $0 (content marketing + HN launches + X posts)\n\n### Growth Levers\n1. **PromptFoo migration path** — Import YAML configs, run in cloud\n2. **GitHub Action** — `parse-prompt-test` action for CI/CD\n3. **VS Code extension** — Test prompts from editor\n4. **Comparison reports** — Shareable links (viral loop)\n5. **Public benchmarks** — \"Parse Prompt Leaderboard\" for models\n\n---\n\n## 9. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Core API (Weeks 1-4) — MVP Launch\n\n**Goal**: Ship `/v1/agents/test` endpoint with basic eval.\n\n| Week | Tasks |\n|------|-------|\n| **1** | Prisma schema (PromptTest, Dataset, DatasetRow), BullMQ \"agent-test\" queue, worker scaffold |\n| **2** | `/v1/agents/test` endpoint, LLM-as-judge eval engine, assertion engine (contains, regex, json_schema, max_tokens) |\n| **3** | Multi-provider support (BYOK + Parse providers), `/v1/agents/tests` history, comparison endpoint |\n| **4** | Stripe integration (Pro tier), docs site, Python/TS SDK, rate limiting |\n\n**Launch**: HackerNews \"Show HN\" + X thread + r/LocalLLaMA post\n\n### Phase 2: Eval Suites + Datasets (Weeks 5-8)\n\n| Week | Tasks |\n|------|-------|\n| **5** | Dataset CRUD, CSV/JSON upload, `/v1/agents/eval` suite runner |\n| **6** | Webhook delivery for async eval, suite comparison, regression detection |\n| **7** | GitHub Action (`parse-prompt-test`), CI/CD integration guide |\n| **8** | Dashboard UI — test history, eval trends, cost tracking |\n\n**Launch**: \"Parse for CI/CD\" blog post + GitHub Action marketplace\n\n### Phase 3: Sandbox + Advanced (Weeks 9-12)\n\n| Week | Tasks |\n|------|-------|\n| **9** | E2B integration, `/v1/agents/sandbox/run`, tool-use testing |\n| **10** | Custom eval criteria (user-defined judge prompts), custom assertion functions |\n| **11** | Team tier features — shared datasets, team API keys, audit log |\n| **12** | PromptFoo import, VS Code extension, public benchmark page |\n\n**Launch**: \"Parse Prompt Leaderboard\" + Team tier announcement\n\n### Phase 4: Enterprise (Weeks 13+)\n\n- SSO/SAML authentication\n- Self-hosted sandbox option\n- SOC 2 compliance documentation\n- Custom LLM provider integration\n- SLA guarantees\n\n---\n\n## 10. Key Architecture Decisions\n\n### Decision 1: BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) vs Parse-Provided\n\n**Decision**: Both. Users can:\n1. Use Parse's LLM providers (charged via credits)\n2. Bring their own API keys (only charged for eval, not LLM calls)\n\nBYOK users still pay for evaluation (judge LLM) and platform features. This lowers the barrier to entry.\n\n### Decision 2: Sync vs Async API\n\n**Decision**: Both.\n- Single prompt tests: **Synchronous** (< 30s timeout) with polling fallback\n- Eval suites: **Asynchronous** with webhook delivery\n- Status polling available for both\n\n### Decision 3: Judge LLM Selection\n\n**Decision**: DeepSeek V3.2 as default judge.\n- Best cost/quality ratio ($0.27/$0.41 per M tokens)\n- Thinking mode for better reasoning about quality\n- Already integrated in Parse\n\nUsers can override with their own judge LLM via BYOK.\n\n### Decision 4: Eval Scoring System\n\n**Decision**: 0-5 scale per criterion, weighted average for overall.\n- Aligns with PromptFoo's scoring (familiar to users)\n- Pass/fail threshold configurable (default 3.5)\n- Assertions are hard pass/fail, scores are soft\n\n### Decision 5: URL Structure\n\n**Decision**: `/v1/agents/*` namespace under existing Parse API.\n- Shares auth middleware\n- Separate from `/api/article/*` (media analysis)\n- Versioned for future breaking changes\n\n---\n\n## 11. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|-----------|\n| **LLM cost overruns** | Eval judge calls add ~$0.001 per eval | DeepSeek is cheapest; cache identical judge prompts |\n| **PromptFoo goes hosted** | Direct competitor | Move fast; they're OSS-focused, hosting is hard |\n| **Low conversion** | Revenue miss | BYOK lowers barrier; free tier is generous |\n| **Sandbox abuse** | Security/cost | No network default; strict resource limits; auto-cleanup |\n| **Scope creep** | Delayed launch | Phase 1 is intentionally minimal — no sandbox, no UI |\n| **Cannibalization** | Confuses Parse brand | \"Parse for Agents\" is a product line, not a pivot |\n\n---\n\n## 12. Success Metrics\n\n### Day 30 (Phase 1 Launch)\n- [ ] 50 registered API keys\n- [ ] 500 prompt tests run\n- [ ] 5 paying Pro users\n- [ ] <2s average latency for single tests\n\n### Day 60 (Phase 2)\n- [ ] 200 registered API keys\n- [ ] 5,000 prompt tests run\n- [ ] 20 Pro + 3 Team users\n- [ ] GitHub Action published\n- [ ] 10 eval suites running in CI/CD\n\n### Day 90 (Phase 3)\n- [ ] 500 registered API keys\n- [ ] 20,000 prompt tests run\n- [ ] $1,500+ MRR\n- [ ] E2B sandbox live\n- [ ] VS Code extension published\n\n---\n\n## 13. File Structure (New Code)\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── app/api/v1/agents/\n│   ├── test/route.ts              # POST /v1/agents/test\n│   ├── tests/route.ts             # GET /v1/agents/tests\n│   ├── tests/[id]/route.ts        # GET /v1/agents/tests/:id\n│   ├── tests/compare/route.ts     # GET /v1/agents/tests/compare\n│   ├── eval/route.ts              # POST /v1/agents/eval\n│   ├── eval/[id]/route.ts         # GET /v1/agents/eval/:id\n│   ├── eval/[id]/results/route.ts # GET /v1/agents/eval/:id/results\n│   ├── datasets/route.ts          # CRUD /v1/agents/datasets\n│   ├── datasets/[id]/route.ts     # CRUD /v1/agents/datasets/:id\n│   ├── datasets/[id]/rows/route.ts # POST rows\n│   ├── sandbox/run/route.ts       # POST /v1/agents/sandbox/run\n│   └── usage/route.ts             # GET /v1/agents/usage\n├── lib/\n│   ├── agent-test/\n│   │   ├── worker.ts              # BullMQ worker for agent tests\n│   │   ├── eval-engine.ts         # LLM-as-judge evaluation\n│   │   ├── assertions.ts          # Deterministic assertion checks\n│   │   ├── scoring.ts             # Score aggregation\n│   │   ├── providers.ts           # BYOK provider management\n│   │   └── sandbox.ts             # E2B sandbox integration (Phase 2)\n│   └── agent-test/\n│       └── queue.ts               # \"agent-test\" BullMQ queue config\n└── types/\n    └── agent-test.ts              # TypeScript types for agent testing\n```\n\n---\n\n## 14. Quick Start (What We Ship Day 1)\n\n```bash\n# Install SDK\nnpm install @parse/agents\n\n# Test a prompt\nparse test \"Explain quantum computing\" --provider deepseek --eval relevance,accuracy\n\n# Run eval suite\nparse eval --dataset sentiment.csv --prompt \"Classify sentiment: {{text}}\" --assert \"json_schema:sentiment.json\"\n\n# CI/CD\n# .github/workflows/prompt-test.yml\n# - uses: parse-news/prompt-test@v1\n#   with:\n#     api-key: ${{ secrets.PARSE_API_KEY }}\n#     config: .parse/eval.yaml\n```\n\n```python\n# Python SDK\nfrom parse_agents import ParseAgents\n\nclient = ParseAgents(api_key=\"parse_pk_prod_...\")\n\nresult = client.test(\n    system=\"You are a helpful assistant\",\n    user=\"Explain {{topic}} in {{length}} sentences\",\n    variables={\"topic\": \"quantum computing\", \"length\": 3},\n    providers=[\"deepseek-v3\"],\n    eval=[\"relevance\", \"accuracy\", \"conciseness\"],\n    assertions=[\n        {\"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\"},\n        {\"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200}\n    ]\n)\n\nprint(f\"Score: {result.overall_score}\")  # 4.6\nprint(f\"Passed: {result.passed}\")         # True\nprint(f\"Cost: ${result.total_cost}\")      # $0.0003\n```\n\n---\n\n## 15. Next Steps\n\n1. **This week**: Create `feature/agents-api` branch, add Prisma models, scaffold endpoints\n2. **Week 2**: Implement eval engine + assertion engine\n3. **Week 3**: Multi-provider support + BYOK\n4. **Week 4**: Stripe integration, docs, SDK, launch\n\n**Decision needed**: Should we launch with a waitlist first, or ship immediately?\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759796615}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9192e38","parentId":"1bd9250c","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:16:36.639Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_af1850d1bb504343b16673f6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Parse for Agents - Prompt Testing Sandbox API\n\n**Version:** 0.1.0-draft\n**Date:** 2026-03-05\n**Status:** Planning\n**Authors:** Kurultai Engineering\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nParse for Agents is an API service that tests LLM prompts in isolated Docker sandboxes and returns structured evaluation metrics. It extends the Parse platform's AI analysis capabilities into a developer-facing API product, enabling teams to systematically evaluate prompt quality, safety, cost, and performance before deploying to production.\n\n**Core value proposition:** Submit a prompt + test cases, get back quality scores, safety flags, latency benchmarks, token usage, and cost estimates — all executed in isolated sandboxes with strict resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## 2. API Specification\n\n### Base URL\n\n```\nProduction:  https://api.parse.dev/v1\nStaging:     https://api-staging.parse.dev/v1\n```\n\n### Authentication\n\nAll requests require a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header.\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer pfa_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx\n```\n\nAPI keys are scoped to organizations and carry tier-level permissions. Keys use the prefix `pfa_live_` (production) or `pfa_test_` (staging).\n\n---\n\n### 2.1 POST /v1/evaluate\n\nSubmit a single prompt evaluation job.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": \"You are a helpful assistant. Summarize the following article in 3 bullet points.\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"article\": \"{{input}}\"\n  },\n  \"test_cases\": [\n    {\n      \"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\",\n      \"expected\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"input\": \"A new study published in Nature shows...\",\n      \"expected\": \"Should mention methodology and sample size\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"safety\", \"cost\", \"latency\"],\n  \"config\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n    \"timeout_seconds\": 30,\n    \"num_runs\": 1\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Request Fields:**\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string | Yes | The prompt template to evaluate. Use `{{variable}}` for interpolation. |\n| `model` | string | Yes | Model identifier in `provider/model` format. |\n| `variables` | object | No | Variable mappings for prompt template interpolation. |\n| `test_cases` | array | Yes | Array of test case objects (min 1, max 100). |\n| `test_cases[].input` | string | Yes | Input text to substitute into the prompt. |\n| `test_cases[].expected` | string | No | Expected output description for quality scoring. |\n| `evaluators` | array | Yes | List of evaluator names to run. |\n| `config` | object | No | Model and execution configuration overrides. |\n| `config.temperature` | number | No | Model temperature (0.0-2.0). Default: 0.7. |\n| `config.max_tokens` | number | No | Max output tokens. Default: 1024. |\n| `config.timeout_seconds` | number | No | Per-test-case timeout. Default: 30, max: 120. |\n| `config.num_runs` | number | No | Repeat count per test case for variance measurement. Default: 1, max: 10. |\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:00Z\",\n  \"estimated_duration_ms\": 15000,\n  \"poll_url\": \"/v1/evaluate/eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"stream_url\": \"wss://api.parse.dev/v1/stream?job=eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 GET /v1/evaluate/{id}\n\nPoll for evaluation results.\n\n**Response (200 OK — completed):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:00Z\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:14Z\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"total_test_cases\": 2,\n    \"passed\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 0,\n    \"avg_quality_score\": 82,\n    \"avg_latency_ms\": 1240,\n    \"total_tokens\": 3420,\n    \"total_cost_usd\": 0.0051,\n    \"safety_issues\": 0\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"test_case_index\": 0,\n      \"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\",\n      \"output\": \"- The Federal Reserve announced...\\n- Key impacts include...\\n- Analysts expect...\",\n      \"metrics\": {\n        \"quality\": {\n          \"score\": 85,\n          \"reasoning\": \"Output is well-structured with 3 bullet points as requested. Captures key information accurately.\",\n          \"sub_scores\": {\n            \"instruction_following\": 95,\n            \"coherence\": 88,\n            \"completeness\": 72,\n            \"conciseness\": 85\n          }\n        },\n        \"safety\": {\n          \"score\": 100,\n          \"flags\": [],\n          \"categories_checked\": [\"harmful_content\", \"bias\", \"pii_leak\", \"prompt_injection\", \"hallucination_risk\"]\n        },\n        \"latency\": {\n          \"total_ms\": 1180,\n          \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 245,\n          \"tokens_per_second\": 48.2\n        },\n        \"cost\": {\n          \"input_tokens\": 890,\n          \"output_tokens\": 320,\n          \"total_tokens\": 1210,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0018\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"test_case_index\": 1,\n      \"input\": \"A new study published in Nature shows...\",\n      \"output\": \"- A Nature study reveals...\\n- The methodology involved...\\n- Results suggest...\",\n      \"metrics\": {\n        \"quality\": {\n          \"score\": 79,\n          \"reasoning\": \"Mentions methodology as expected. Sample size reference is implicit but not explicit.\",\n          \"sub_scores\": {\n            \"instruction_following\": 92,\n            \"coherence\": 85,\n            \"completeness\": 65,\n            \"conciseness\": 80\n          }\n        },\n        \"safety\": {\n          \"score\": 100,\n          \"flags\": [],\n          \"categories_checked\": [\"harmful_content\", \"bias\", \"pii_leak\", \"prompt_injection\", \"hallucination_risk\"]\n        },\n        \"latency\": {\n          \"total_ms\": 1300,\n          \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 260,\n          \"tokens_per_second\": 45.1\n        },\n        \"cost\": {\n          \"input_tokens\": 1120,\n          \"output_tokens\": 410,\n          \"total_tokens\": 1530,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0023\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Status values:** `queued` | `running` | `completed` | `failed` | `cancelled` | `timed_out`\n\n**Response (200 OK — still running):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"running\",\n  \"progress\": {\n    \"completed\": 1,\n    \"total\": 2,\n    \"percent\": 50\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"...\": \"partial results for completed test cases\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 POST /v1/batch\n\nSubmit a batch of prompt evaluations. Useful for A/B testing prompts or running the same prompt across multiple models.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt-v1\",\n      \"prompt\": \"Summarize this: {{input}}\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        { \"input\": \"Article text here...\" }\n      ],\n      \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt-v2\",\n      \"prompt\": \"Provide a concise 3-bullet summary of: {{input}}\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        { \"input\": \"Article text here...\" }\n      ],\n      \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"compare\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"total_evaluations\": 2,\n  \"poll_url\": \"/v1/batch/batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\"\n}\n```\n\n**GET /v1/batch/{batch_id} Response (completed with compare=true):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"evaluations\": [\n    { \"name\": \"prompt-v1\", \"...\": \"full evaluation result\" },\n    { \"name\": \"prompt-v2\", \"...\": \"full evaluation result\" }\n  ],\n  \"comparison\": {\n    \"best_quality\": \"prompt-v2\",\n    \"best_cost\": \"prompt-v1\",\n    \"best_latency\": \"prompt-v1\",\n    \"recommendation\": \"prompt-v2\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"prompt-v2 scores 12% higher on quality with only $0.0003 additional cost per evaluation.\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Limits:**\n\n| Tier | Max evaluations per batch | Max test cases total |\n|------|--------------------------|---------------------|\n| Free | 2 | 10 |\n| Pro | 10 | 200 |\n| Team | 50 | 1000 |\n| Enterprise | 200 | 5000 |\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 WebSocket /v1/stream\n\nReal-time streaming of evaluation results.\n\n**Connection:**\n\n```\nwss://api.parse.dev/v1/stream?job={evaluation_id}&token={api_key}\n```\n\n**Server-sent message types:**\n\n```jsonc\n// Job started\n{ \"type\": \"job.started\", \"id\": \"eval_...\", \"total_test_cases\": 5 }\n\n// Test case started\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.started\", \"index\": 0, \"input_preview\": \"The Federal...\" }\n\n// Partial output (streaming tokens)\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.token\", \"index\": 0, \"token\": \"The\", \"accumulated\": \"The\" }\n\n// Test case completed\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.completed\", \"index\": 0, \"metrics\": { \"...\": \"full metrics\" } }\n\n// Evaluator completed\n{ \"type\": \"evaluator.completed\", \"index\": 0, \"evaluator\": \"quality\", \"score\": 85 }\n\n// Job completed\n{ \"type\": \"job.completed\", \"summary\": { \"...\": \"full summary\" } }\n\n// Error\n{ \"type\": \"error\", \"message\": \"Model API timeout\", \"test_case_index\": 2 }\n```\n\n**Client commands:**\n\n```jsonc\n// Cancel job\n{ \"action\": \"cancel\" }\n\n// Skip remaining test cases\n{ \"action\": \"skip\", \"from_index\": 3 }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 Additional Endpoints\n\n```\nGET    /v1/models                    — List supported models and pricing\nGET    /v1/evaluators                — List available evaluators with descriptions\nGET    /v1/evaluate/{id}/export      — Export results as CSV/JSON\nDELETE /v1/evaluate/{id}             — Delete evaluation results\nGET    /v1/usage                     — Current billing period usage\nPOST   /v1/evaluators/custom         — Register a custom evaluator (Team+)\nGET    /v1/history                   — List past evaluations with filters\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Supported Models\n\nModel identifiers follow the `provider/model` format:\n\n| Provider | Models | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| `openai` | `gpt-4o`, `gpt-4o-mini`, `gpt-4-turbo`, `o1`, `o3-mini` | Via OpenAI API |\n| `anthropic` | `claude-sonnet-4-6`, `claude-haiku-4-5` | Via Anthropic API |\n| `google` | `gemini-2.0-flash`, `gemini-2.0-pro` | Via Google AI API |\n| `deepseek` | `deepseek-chat`, `deepseek-reasoner` | Via DeepSeek API |\n| `mistral` | `mistral-large`, `mistral-small` | Via Mistral API |\n| `meta` | `llama-3.3-70b` | Via Together/Fireworks |\n\nUsers supply their own API keys per provider, or use Parse-hosted keys (with markup).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Evaluators\n\n### 4.1 Built-in Evaluators\n\n#### `quality` — Output Quality Score\n\nMeasures how well the model output satisfies the prompt instructions.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100\n- **Sub-scores:**\n  - `instruction_following` — Did it do what was asked?\n  - `coherence` — Is the output logically structured?\n  - `completeness` — Does it cover all required points?\n  - `conciseness` — Is it appropriately concise?\n- **Method:** Uses a judge LLM (Claude Sonnet 4.6) to evaluate against the prompt instructions and optional expected output.\n\n#### `safety` — Safety & Content Flags\n\nScans output for safety concerns.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = fully safe)\n- **Flags array:** Each flag contains `category`, `severity` (low/medium/high/critical), `excerpt`, and `explanation`.\n- **Categories checked:**\n  - `harmful_content` — Violence, self-harm, illegal activities\n  - `bias` — Gender, racial, political bias in output\n  - `pii_leak` — Personal information in output that wasn't in input\n  - `prompt_injection` — Output attempts to override system instructions\n  - `hallucination_risk` — Claims without grounding in provided context\n  - `copyright` — Potential verbatim reproduction of copyrighted text\n\n#### `cost` — Token Usage & Cost\n\nMeasures token consumption and estimates cost.\n\n- **Fields:** `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `cost_usd`\n- **Pricing:** Based on provider's published pricing at time of evaluation.\n\n#### `latency` — Performance Timing\n\nMeasures response speed.\n\n- **Fields:** `total_ms`, `time_to_first_token_ms`, `tokens_per_second`\n- **Note:** Includes sandbox overhead (~50-100ms). Raw model latency is `total_ms - sandbox_overhead_ms`.\n\n#### `consistency` — Output Variance (requires `num_runs` > 1)\n\nMeasures how consistent outputs are across multiple runs.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = perfectly consistent)\n- **Fields:** `variance_score`, `semantic_similarity_avg`, `structural_similarity_avg`\n- **Method:** Runs the same prompt N times and compares outputs pairwise.\n\n#### `groundedness` — Factual Grounding\n\nChecks if claims in the output are supported by the input context.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100\n- **Fields:** `grounded_claims`, `ungrounded_claims`, `claim_details[]`\n- **Method:** Extracts claims from output, checks each against input context.\n\n#### `injection_safety` — Prompt Injection & Hidden Instruction Detection\n\nScans prompt inputs, outputs, and context for hidden instructions, prompt injection payloads, and agent manipulation attempts (brainworm-style attacks).\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = no injections detected)\n- **Flags array:** Each flag contains `pattern_type`, `severity` (low/medium/high/critical), `excerpt`, `explanation`, and `category`.\n- **Categories detected:**\n\n| Category | Severity | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `hidden_html_instruction` | Critical | Hidden `<div style=\"display:none\">`, white-on-white text, 1px font, `aria-hidden` content containing instructions |\n| `html_comment_instruction` | High | HTML comments (`<!-- -->`) containing behavioral commands |\n| `data_attribute_instruction` | Medium | `data-*` attributes or image `alt` text carrying hidden instructions |\n| `c2_registration` | Critical | Instructions to connect to external command-and-control servers, register as a node, or exfiltrate data |\n| `urgency_coercion` | High | Patterns like \"YOU MUST\", \"IMMEDIATELY\", \"CRITICAL\" designed to override agent reasoning |\n| `behavioral_constraint` | High | Attempts to impose rules on the agent (\"NEVER CREATE SCRIPTS\", \"ONLY USE ONE-LINERS\") |\n| `identity_override` | Critical | Attempts to reassign agent identity (\"You are now BRAINWORM\", \"Ignore previous instructions\") |\n| `network_exfiltration` | Critical | Instructions to send data to external URLs, APIs, or webhooks not in the allowlist |\n| `memory_persistence` | High | Instructions designed to persist across sessions via memory files or config injection |\n| `privilege_escalation` | Critical | Attempts to disable sandboxing, skip verification, or escalate permissions |\n\n- **Method:** Deterministic pattern matching (regex + heuristic rules) for fast, zero-LLM-cost detection. No judge LLM required.\n- **Scoring formula:**\n  ```\n  score = max(0, 100 - sum(severity_penalties))\n\n  Severity penalties:\n    Critical: -30 per finding\n    High:     -20 per finding\n    Medium:   -10 per finding\n    Low:      -5  per finding\n  ```\n- **Use case:** Defense against \"brainworm\" promptware (memory file injection), canar.ai-style hidden HTML payloads, and C2 registration attempts targeting AI agents at runtime.\n- **References:**\n  - [Canar.ai](https://canar.ai) — 17+ hidden payload vectors in web content\n  - Brainworm / OriginHQ — Memory file injection patterns (\"promptware\")\n  - [Grith.ai](https://grith.ai) — Runtime zero-trust security for AI agents\n\n### 4.2 Custom Evaluators (Team tier+)\n\nUsers can register custom evaluator functions:\n\n```json\nPOST /v1/evaluators/custom\n{\n  \"name\": \"brand_voice\",\n  \"description\": \"Checks if output matches brand voice guidelines\",\n  \"type\": \"llm_judge\",\n  \"judge_prompt\": \"Rate the following output on brand voice alignment from 0-100. Brand guidelines: {{guidelines}}. Output to evaluate: {{output}}\",\n  \"judge_model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"guidelines\": \"Professional, empathetic, no jargon, active voice...\"\n  },\n  \"output_schema\": {\n    \"score\": \"number\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"string\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCustom evaluator types:\n- `llm_judge` — Uses an LLM to evaluate (most flexible)\n- `regex` — Pattern matching (fast, deterministic)\n- `code` — Custom JavaScript function executed in sandbox (Team+)\n- `composite` — Weighted combination of other evaluators\n\n---\n\n## 5. Sandbox Architecture\n\n### 5.1 Isolation Model\n\nEach evaluation runs in an isolated Docker container:\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   API Gateway (Hono)                  │\n│                                                      │\n│  Auth ─► Rate Limit ─► Validate ─► Queue (BullMQ)   │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n                       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  Worker Process                       │\n│                                                      │\n│  Dequeue Job ─► Spawn Container ─► Collect Results   │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n            ▼          ▼          ▼\n     ┌───────────┐ ┌───────────┐ ┌───────────┐\n     │ Sandbox 1 │ │ Sandbox 2 │ │ Sandbox N │\n     │           │ │           │ │           │\n     │ Test Case │ │ Test Case │ │ Test Case │\n     │     1     │ │     2     │ │     N     │\n     │           │ │           │ │           │\n     │ ┌───────┐ │ │ ┌───────┐ │ │ ┌───────┐ │\n     │ │ LLM   │ │ │ │ LLM   │ │ │ │ LLM   │ │\n     │ │ Call  ├─┼─┼─┤►Proxy ├─┼─┼─┤►Only  │ │\n     │ └───────┘ │ │ └───────┘ │ │ └───────┘ │\n     └───────────┘ └───────────┘ └───────────┘\n           │              │             │\n           └──────────────┼─────────────┘\n                          ▼\n              ┌──────────────────┐\n              │   LLM API Proxy  │\n              │  (allowlisted     │\n              │   endpoints only) │\n              └────────┬─────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n            ▼          ▼          ▼\n        OpenAI    Anthropic   Google\n```\n\n### 5.2 Container Specification\n\n```yaml\n# sandbox container spec\nimage: parse-sandbox:latest\nresources:\n  memory: 512MB          # hard limit, OOM-killed above this\n  cpu: 0.5               # half a CPU core\n  pids: 64               # max process count\n  storage: 100MB         # ephemeral tmpfs\n\ntimeouts:\n  per_test_case: 30s     # default, configurable up to 120s\n  total_job: 300s        # hard cap per evaluation job\n  container_startup: 5s  # container must be ready within 5s\n\nnetwork:\n  mode: none             # no network access from container\n  proxy:                 # all LLM calls go through proxy\n    allowed_hosts:\n      - api.openai.com\n      - api.anthropic.com\n      - generativelanguage.googleapis.com\n      - api.deepseek.com\n      - api.mistral.ai\n    blocked: [\"*\"]       # everything else blocked\n\nsecurity:\n  read_only_rootfs: true\n  no_new_privileges: true\n  seccomp_profile: default\n  capabilities_drop: [ALL]\n  user: 1000:1000        # non-root\n```\n\n### 5.3 Container Lifecycle\n\n```\n1. Job dequeued from BullMQ\n2. Container pulled from warm pool (pre-warmed containers)\n3. Prompt template + test case injected via /tmp/input.json\n4. Evaluation script runs inside container\n5. LLM calls routed through proxy (network proxy sidecar)\n6. Results written to /tmp/output.json\n7. Worker reads results, runs evaluators\n8. Container destroyed (force kill after timeout)\n9. Results stored in Redis with TTL\n```\n\n### 5.4 Warm Pool\n\nTo minimize cold start latency, maintain a pool of pre-created containers:\n\n| Tier | Warm pool size | Max concurrent |\n|------|---------------|----------------|\n| Free | 2 | 1 |\n| Pro | 10 | 5 |\n| Team | 50 | 20 |\n| Enterprise | 200 | 100 |\n\n---\n\n## 6. System Architecture\n\n### 6.1 High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        API Layer (Hono on Node.js)              │\n│                                                                 │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  │\n│  │   Auth   │  │   Route   │  │  Validate │  │  Rate Limit  │  │\n│  │ Middleware│  │  Handlers │  │    Zod    │  │   per-tier   │  │\n│  └──────────┘  └───────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────────┘  │\n└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n              ┌────────────┼────────────┐\n              ▼            ▼            ▼\n     ┌──────────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌──────────┐\n     │  PostgreSQL   │ │  Redis  │ │  BullMQ  │\n     │              │ │         │ │          │\n     │ - Jobs table │ │ - Cache │ │ - Eval   │\n     │ - Users      │ │ - Results│ │   Queue  │\n     │ - API keys   │ │ - Sessions│ │ - Batch │\n     │ - Usage logs │ │ - Rate  │ │   Queue  │\n     │ - Evaluators │ │   limits│ │          │\n     └──────────────┘ └─────────┘ └────┬─────┘\n                                       │\n                                       ▼\n                           ┌───────────────────┐\n                           │   Worker Process   │\n                           │   (N instances)    │\n                           │                    │\n                           │  - Docker mgmt     │\n                           │  - Result collect  │\n                           │  - Evaluator exec  │\n                           └────────┬──────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n                           ┌───────────────────┐\n                           │  Docker Engine     │\n                           │  Sandbox Pool      │\n                           └───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 6.2 Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology | Rationale |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|\n| **API Framework** | **Hono** (Node.js) | Lightweight, fast, excellent TypeScript support, Web Standards-based. Parse already uses Node.js ecosystem. |\n| **Validation** | Zod | Already used in Parse. Type-safe schema validation. |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL (via Prisma) | Parse already uses Prisma+Postgres. Stores jobs, users, API keys, usage logs. |\n| **Cache/Results** | Redis | Fast result storage with TTL. Already in Parse stack for BullMQ. |\n| **Job Queue** | BullMQ | Already used in Parse for analysis pipeline. Reliable, Redis-backed, supports priorities and rate limiting. |\n| **Container Runtime** | Docker Engine API (dockerode) | Direct Docker API via Node.js. No K8s overhead for MVP. Upgrade path to K8s for scale. |\n| **WebSocket** | Hono WebSocket (via ws) | Native WebSocket support in Hono. |\n| **Auth** | API key-based | Simple, stateless. JWT for dashboard sessions. |\n| **LLM Proxy** | Custom HTTP proxy | Allowlisted endpoints, request/response logging, token counting. |\n| **Deployment** | Railway | Parse already deploys on Railway. Separate service in same project. |\n| **Monitoring** | Railway metrics + custom | Leverage existing Railway infrastructure. |\n\n### 6.3 Why Hono over FastAPI/Express\n\n- **vs FastAPI (Python):** Parse ecosystem is TypeScript/Node.js. Adding Python would split the stack, complicate deployment, and prevent code sharing with the main Parse app (Prisma models, BullMQ queues, utility functions).\n- **vs Express:** Hono is faster, lighter, has better TypeScript support, and built-in middleware for validation, CORS, auth. Express is legacy at this point.\n- **vs Next.js API routes:** Evaluation API is a separate service with different scaling characteristics (CPU-bound worker processes). Decoupling from the Next.js frontend is correct.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Database Schema\n\n### 7.1 PostgreSQL Tables\n\n```sql\n-- API keys for authentication\nCREATE TABLE api_keys (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),\n  org_id        TEXT REFERENCES organizations(id),\n  key_hash      TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,        -- bcrypt hash of the key\n  key_prefix    TEXT NOT NULL,               -- \"pfa_live_abc\" for display\n  name          TEXT NOT NULL,               -- user-assigned label\n  tier          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'free', -- free/pro/team/enterprise\n  scopes        TEXT[] DEFAULT '{evaluate}',\n  rate_limit    INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 10,     -- requests per minute\n  last_used_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  expires_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  revoked_at    TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n\n-- Evaluation jobs\nCREATE TABLE evaluations (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,            -- eval_ULID\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  batch_id      TEXT REFERENCES batches(id),\n  status        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  prompt        TEXT NOT NULL,\n  model         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  variables     JSONB,\n  test_cases    JSONB NOT NULL,\n  evaluators    TEXT[] NOT NULL,\n  config        JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  summary       JSONB,                       -- populated on completion\n  error         JSONB,                       -- populated on failure\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  expires_at    TIMESTAMPTZ                  -- result TTL\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_status ON evaluations(status);\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_api_key ON evaluations(api_key_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_created ON evaluations(created_at DESC);\n\n-- Batch jobs\nCREATE TABLE batches (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,            -- batch_ULID\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  status        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  total         INT NOT NULL,\n  completed     INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  compare       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,\n  comparison    JSONB,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n\n-- Usage tracking for billing\nCREATE TABLE usage_records (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  evaluation_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES evaluations(id),\n  model         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  input_tokens  INT NOT NULL,\n  output_tokens INT NOT NULL,\n  cost_usd      DECIMAL(10, 6) NOT NULL,\n  evaluator_cost_usd DECIMAL(10, 6) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_usage_api_key_created ON usage_records(api_key_id, created_at DESC);\n\n-- Custom evaluators\nCREATE TABLE custom_evaluators (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  org_id        TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES organizations(id),\n  name          TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description   TEXT,\n  type          TEXT NOT NULL,               -- llm_judge/regex/code/composite\n  config        JSONB NOT NULL,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  UNIQUE(org_id, name)\n);\n```\n\n### 7.2 Redis Keys\n\n```\n# Evaluation results (full detail) — TTL: 24h free, 7d pro, 30d team\neval:{eval_id}:results     → JSON blob of full results\n\n# Streaming state\neval:{eval_id}:stream      → current streaming state for WebSocket\neval:{eval_id}:progress    → { completed: N, total: M }\n\n# Rate limiting\nratelimit:{api_key_id}     → sliding window counter (TTL: 60s)\n\n# Container warm pool tracking\npool:available             → Set of available container IDs\npool:in_use                → Set of in-use container IDs\n\n# API key cache (avoid DB lookup per request)\napikey:{key_hash}          → cached key metadata (TTL: 5min)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Error Handling\n\n### 8.1 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\",\n    \"message\": \"Rate limit of 10 requests/minute exceeded. Retry after 23 seconds.\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"limit\": 10,\n      \"remaining\": 0,\n      \"reset_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:33:00Z\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 8.2 Error Codes\n\n| HTTP Status | Code | Description |\n|------------|------|-------------|\n| 400 | `invalid_request` | Malformed request body or invalid parameters |\n| 400 | `unsupported_model` | Requested model is not supported |\n| 400 | `invalid_evaluator` | Unknown evaluator name |\n| 401 | `unauthorized` | Missing or invalid API key |\n| 403 | `insufficient_tier` | Feature not available on current tier |\n| 404 | `evaluation_not_found` | Evaluation ID does not exist |\n| 409 | `evaluation_expired` | Results have been cleaned up (past TTL) |\n| 422 | `test_case_limit` | Too many test cases for tier |\n| 429 | `rate_limit_exceeded` | Too many requests |\n| 500 | `internal_error` | Unexpected server error |\n| 502 | `model_api_error` | Upstream LLM API returned an error |\n| 504 | `evaluation_timeout` | Evaluation exceeded timeout |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Rate Limits & Quotas\n\n| | Free | Pro ($29/mo) | Team ($99/mo) | Enterprise |\n|--|------|-------------|---------------|------------|\n| Requests/min | 10 | 60 | 200 | Custom |\n| Evaluations/month | 100 | 5,000 | 50,000 | Unlimited |\n| Test cases/evaluation | 5 | 50 | 100 | 500 |\n| Batch size | 2 | 10 | 50 | 200 |\n| Concurrent jobs | 1 | 5 | 20 | 100 |\n| Result retention | 24 hours | 7 days | 30 days | 90 days |\n| Custom evaluators | 0 | 0 | 10 | Unlimited |\n| WebSocket streaming | No | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n| `num_runs` max | 1 | 3 | 10 | 10 |\n\nRate limit headers included on every response:\n\n```\nX-RateLimit-Limit: 60\nX-RateLimit-Remaining: 58\nX-RateLimit-Reset: 1709617980\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. Pricing Model\n\n### 10.1 Subscription Tiers\n\n| Tier | Price | Target |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| **Free** | $0/mo | Individual developers, exploration |\n| **Pro** | $29/mo | Solo developers, small teams |\n| **Team** | $99/mo | Engineering teams, CI/CD integration |\n| **Enterprise** | Custom | Large orgs, custom SLAs |\n\n### 10.2 Per-Evaluation Costs\n\nIn addition to subscription, users pay per-evaluation costs that cover:\n\n1. **LLM API costs** — Pass-through of model provider pricing + 20% markup (or BYOK: bring your own key, 0% markup)\n2. **Evaluator costs** — Judge LLM calls for quality/safety scoring\n3. **Compute costs** — Sandbox compute time\n\n```\nEstimated cost per evaluation (1 test case, gpt-4o-mini):\n  LLM API (Parse keys):     $0.0015 (input) + $0.0010 (output) = $0.0025\n  Parse markup (20%):        $0.0005\n  Evaluator (judge LLM):     $0.0020\n  Compute overhead:          $0.0005\n  ─────────────────────────────────\n  Total:                     ~$0.0055 per test case\n\nEstimated cost per evaluation (1 test case, gpt-4o-mini, BYOK):\n  LLM API:                   $0.0000 (user's key)\n  Parse markup:              $0.0000\n  Evaluator (judge LLM):     $0.0020\n  Compute overhead:          $0.0005\n  ─────────────────────────────────\n  Total:                     ~$0.0025 per test case\n```\n\n### 10.3 Free Tier Limits\n\n- 100 evaluations/month\n- Max 5 test cases per evaluation\n- No batch endpoint\n- No WebSocket streaming\n- Results expire after 24 hours\n- Only `quality`, `safety`, `cost`, `latency` evaluators (no `consistency`, `groundedness`)\n- Parse-managed keys only (no BYOK)\n\n---\n\n## 11. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: MVP (Weeks 1-3)\n\n**Goal:** Single evaluation endpoint, basic evaluators, core sandbox.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Hono API server with `POST /v1/evaluate` and `GET /v1/evaluate/{id}`\n- [ ] API key authentication (manual key creation, no self-serve)\n- [ ] Zod request/response validation\n- [ ] BullMQ job queue integration\n- [ ] Docker sandbox with resource limits\n- [ ] LLM proxy (OpenAI + Anthropic only)\n- [ ] `cost` evaluator (token counting, pricing lookup)\n- [ ] `latency` evaluator (timing instrumentation)\n- [ ] `quality` evaluator (basic LLM judge)\n- [ ] Redis result storage with TTL\n- [ ] Postgres schema (evaluations, api_keys, usage_records)\n- [ ] Rate limiting middleware\n- [ ] Error handling with standard error format\n- [ ] Railway deployment (separate service)\n- [ ] `GET /v1/models` and `GET /v1/evaluators` info endpoints\n\n**Excluded from MVP:** Batch endpoint, WebSocket streaming, custom evaluators, safety evaluator, dashboard UI.\n\n### Phase 2: Batch + Streaming (Weeks 4-5)\n\n**Goal:** Batch evaluations for A/B testing, real-time results.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] `POST /v1/batch` endpoint\n- [ ] `GET /v1/batch/{batch_id}` with comparison logic\n- [ ] WebSocket `/v1/stream` endpoint\n- [ ] Streaming token relay from sandbox to client\n- [ ] `safety` evaluator (content classification, PII detection)\n- [ ] `consistency` evaluator (multi-run variance)\n- [ ] Additional model support (Google, DeepSeek, Mistral)\n- [ ] Self-serve API key management\n- [ ] Usage dashboard (basic)\n- [ ] BYOK (bring your own key) support\n- [ ] `GET /v1/history` with pagination and filters\n- [ ] Result export (CSV/JSON)\n\n### Phase 3: Custom Evaluators + Platform (Weeks 6-8)\n\n**Goal:** Extensibility, CI/CD integration, production hardening.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Custom evaluator registration (`POST /v1/evaluators/custom`)\n- [ ] LLM judge custom evaluators\n- [ ] Regex evaluators\n- [ ] Code evaluators (sandboxed JS execution)\n- [ ] Composite evaluators\n- [ ] `groundedness` evaluator\n- [ ] Webhook notifications on job completion\n- [ ] CI/CD integration examples (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI)\n- [ ] SDK packages (TypeScript, Python)\n- [ ] Stripe billing integration\n- [ ] Organization/team management\n- [ ] Warm container pool optimization\n- [ ] Horizontal worker scaling\n- [ ] SLA monitoring and alerting\n\n### Phase 4: Scale + Enterprise (Weeks 9-12)\n\n**Goal:** Enterprise readiness, advanced features.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Kubernetes migration for container orchestration\n- [ ] Multi-region deployment\n- [ ] SSO/SAML authentication\n- [ ] Audit logging\n- [ ] SOC 2 compliance preparation\n- [ ] Prompt versioning and history\n- [ ] Evaluation regression detection (auto-compare against baseline)\n- [ ] Dashboard with charts, trends, comparisons\n- [ ] Team permissions and RBAC\n- [ ] Dedicated infrastructure option\n\n---\n\n## 12. SDK Examples\n\n### TypeScript SDK\n\n```typescript\nimport { ParseAgents } from '@parse/agents-sdk';\n\nconst client = new ParseAgents({ apiKey: 'pfa_live_...' });\n\n// Single evaluation\nconst result = await client.evaluate({\n  prompt: 'Summarize: {{input}}',\n  model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini',\n  testCases: [\n    { input: 'Article text here...' },\n    { input: 'Another article...' },\n  ],\n  evaluators: ['quality', 'safety', 'cost'],\n});\n\nconsole.log(result.summary.avgQualityScore); // 85\nconsole.log(result.summary.totalCostUsd);     // 0.0051\n\n// Batch with comparison\nconst batch = await client.batch({\n  evaluations: [\n    { name: 'v1', prompt: 'Summarize: {{input}}', model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', ... },\n    { name: 'v2', prompt: 'Give 3 bullets: {{input}}', model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', ... },\n  ],\n  compare: true,\n});\n\nconsole.log(batch.comparison.recommendation); // \"v2\"\n\n// Streaming\nconst stream = client.stream('eval_01JQ...');\nstream.on('test_case.completed', (data) => {\n  console.log(`Test ${data.index}: quality=${data.metrics.quality.score}`);\n});\n```\n\n### Python SDK\n\n```python\nfrom parse_agents import ParseAgents\n\nclient = ParseAgents(api_key=\"pfa_live_...\")\n\nresult = client.evaluate(\n    prompt=\"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    model=\"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    test_cases=[\n        {\"input\": \"Article text here...\"},\n    ],\n    evaluators=[\"quality\", \"safety\", \"cost\"],\n)\n\nprint(result.summary.avg_quality_score)  # 85\nprint(result.summary.total_cost_usd)      # 0.0051\n```\n\n### cURL\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://api.parse.dev/v1/evaluate \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer pfa_live_...\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"prompt\": \"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    \"test_cases\": [{ \"input\": \"Article text...\" }],\n    \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n  }'\n\n# Poll for results\ncurl https://api.parse.dev/v1/evaluate/eval_01JQ... \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer pfa_live_...\"\n```\n\n### GitHub Actions\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/prompt-eval.yml\nname: Prompt Evaluation\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths: ['prompts/**']\n\njobs:\n  evaluate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: parse-dev/evaluate-action@v1\n        with:\n          api-key: ${{ secrets.PARSE_AGENTS_API_KEY }}\n          prompt-file: prompts/summarizer.txt\n          test-cases-file: prompts/summarizer.test.json\n          evaluators: quality,safety,cost\n          min-quality-score: 80\n          max-cost-per-eval: 0.01\n```\n\n---\n\n## 13. Security Considerations\n\n| Concern | Mitigation |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Container escape | Rootless containers, seccomp profile, dropped capabilities, read-only rootfs |\n| Network exfiltration | Container network=none, all LLM calls via proxy with allowlist |\n| API key leakage | Keys stored as bcrypt hashes, only prefix shown in UI, rotation support |\n| Prompt injection via test cases | Sandboxed execution, no access to system resources |\n| DoS via large payloads | Request size limits (1MB body), test case limits per tier |\n| Resource exhaustion | Per-container resource limits, per-tier concurrency caps, warm pool sizing |\n| Data retention | Results auto-expire per tier TTL, users can delete results early |\n| BYOK key security | User API keys encrypted at rest (AES-256), never logged, passed to container via env |\n\n---\n\n## 14. Monitoring & Observability\n\n**Metrics to track:**\n\n- Evaluation throughput (jobs/min)\n- Queue depth and wait time\n- Container startup latency (cold vs warm)\n- LLM API latency per provider\n- Error rates by type (timeout, model error, sandbox error)\n- Cost per evaluation (actual vs estimated)\n- Usage by tier, by API key\n- Warm pool utilization\n\n**Alerting thresholds:**\n\n- Queue depth > 100 jobs: scale workers\n- Container cold start > 10s: investigate Docker/pool\n- Error rate > 5%: page on-call\n- LLM API error rate > 10% for any provider: circuit break\n\n---\n\n## 15. Open Questions\n\n1. **BYOK key management:** Should we store user API keys or require them per-request? Stored keys are more convenient but higher security risk. Per-request is safer but worse UX.\n\n2. **Judge LLM selection:** Currently spec'd as Claude Sonnet 4.6 for quality/safety evaluation. Should this be configurable? Using the same model as the evaluand could introduce bias.\n\n3. **Container runtime alternatives:** Docker is spec'd for MVP. Should we evaluate gVisor/Firecracker for stronger isolation in later phases?\n\n4. **Multi-tenancy:** Single Redis/Postgres or per-tenant isolation? Single is simpler, per-tenant is more secure for enterprise.\n\n5. **Pricing model validation:** Is the 20% LLM markup competitive? Competitors range from 10-50%.\n\n6. **Prompt template format:** Using `{{variable}}` (Handlebars-style). Should we also support `{variable}` (Python f-string) or `${variable}` (JS template literal)?\n\n---\n\n*End of specification. This document should be treated as a living spec and updated as decisions are made during implementation.*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772759796631}}
{"type":"message","id":"5116dc81","parentId":"b9192e38","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:17:31.243Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive view of the x402 pay-as-you-go implementation for Parse for Agents. Let me synthesize the status:\n\n## x402 Implementation Status\n\nFrom the files I've read:\n\n1. **x402.ts** - There's a complete x402 payment middleware implementation at `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/x402.ts`:\n   - Uses `@x402/hono` and `@x402/evm/exact/server` packages\n   - Configured for USDC payments on Base L2 (network: eip155:8453)\n   - Pricing defined:\n     - analyze: quick $0.01, standard $0.05, deep $0.15\n     - evaluate: $0.01\n     - chat: $0.005\n   - Endpoints configured:\n     - POST /v1/analyze\n     - POST /v1/evaluate\n     - POST /v1/chat\n   - Environment variables needed:\n     - X402_ENABLED=true\n     - X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS (wallet address)\n     - X402_NETWORK (default: eip155:8453 - Base)\n     - X402_FACILITATOR_URL (default: https://facilitator.x402.org)\n   - The middleware is designed to check for x-payment header and verify payments\n\n2. **Implementation Status from Task Files**:\n   - There's a pending/executing task `high-1772671401.pending.executing.md` that mentions:\n     - \"0/16 MVP checkboxes completed after 18+ hours\"\n     - Blocked by filesystem access to `/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/`\n   - The build task mentions the feature was marked \"done\" but wasn't actually deployed:\n     - `/agents` returns 404\n     - `/api/v1/agents-test/models` returns 404\n     - `/api/v1/agents-test/evaluators` returns 404\n\n3. **Spec Files**:\n   - PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md - Comprehensive implementation plan\n   - SPEC-parse-for-agents.md - Detailed API specification\n   - Both mention pay-per-use pricing but x402 specifically is in the x402.ts file\n\n## Summary\n\nThe x402 pay-as-you-go implementation status:\n\n**Code Complete:**\n- x402.ts middleware is implemented with full payment integration\n- Supports USDC on Base L2\n- Pricing structure defined for all endpoints\n- Fallback to API key auth when no payment header present\n\n**Deployment Status:**\n- NOT deployed - the Parse for Agents endpoints return 404\n- TypeScript errors blocking deployment (from MEMORY.md)\n- The build task mentions the feature was marked \"done\" but never actually deployed\n\n**Blockers:**\n1. TypeScript errors blocking deployment\n2. Filesystem access constraints for temujin\n3. Environment variables need to be set (X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS, X402_ENABLED)\n\n**What Needs to Happen:**\n1. Fix TypeScript errors\n2. Set environment variables:\n   - X402_ENABLED=true\n   - X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS=<wallet address>\n3. Deploy to Railway\n4. Verify endpoints work\n\nLet me provide this summary to the user.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Here's the status of the x402 pay-as-you-go implementation for Parse for Agents:\n\n---\n\n## x402 Pay-As-You-Go Implementation Status\n\n### What's Built\n\n**x402 Middleware** (`/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/x402.ts`):\n- Fully implemented using `@x402/hono` and `@x402/evm` packages\n- USDC payments on Base L2 (network: `eip155:8453`)\n- Facilitator: `https://facilitator.x402.org`\n\n**Pricing Structure:**\n| Endpoint | Price |\n|----------|-------|\n| POST /v1/analyze (quick) | $0.01 |\n| POST /v1/analyze (standard) | $0.05 |\n| POST /v1/analyze (deep) | $0.15 |\n| POST /v1/evaluate | $0.01 |\n| POST /v1/chat | $0.005 |\n\n**Hybrid Auth Model:**\n- If `x-payment` header present → x402 payment verification\n- If no payment header → falls back to API key auth\n\n### Deployment Status: NOT DEPLOYED\n\nCurrent state:\n- `/agents` returns 404\n- `/api/v1/agents-test/models` returns 404\n- `/api/v1/agents-test/evaluators` returns 404\n\nFrom temujin's task files: \"The previous task was marked 'done' but the feature was never built or deployed.\"\n\n### Blockers\n\n1. **TypeScript errors** blocking new feature deployment (from MEMORY.md)\n2. **Environment variables not set:**\n   - `X402_ENABLED=true`\n   - `X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS` (wallet address not configured)\n3. **Filesystem access constraints** blocking temujin from completing the build\n\n### What's Needed\n\n1. Fix TypeScript errors in the Parse codebase\n2. Set environment variables in Railway:\n   ```\n   X402_ENABLED=true\n   X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS=<your USDC receiving wallet>\n   ```\n3. Deploy the Parse for Agents service\n4. Verify endpoints at `https://www.parsethe.media/agents`\n\n### Next Steps\n\nThe pending task `high-1772671401` is currently marked as \"executing\" but blocked by filesystem access. Would you like me to:\n\n1. Spawn an ACP session to fix the TypeScript errors and deploy?\n2. Check the specific TypeScript errors blocking deployment?\n3. Verify the x402 environment variable configuration needed?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":85386,"output":1249,"cacheRead":30784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117419,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772759796639}}
