{"type":"message","id":"9f2660c1","parentId":"eb685be2","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:19:25.700Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Heartbeat check results:\n\n1. **Gateway:** Shows \"Service not installed\" but \"Listening: *:18789\" and \"RPC probe: ok\" - The gateway IS running (port 18789 is active), just not installed as a LaunchAgent service. This is acceptable.\n\n2. **Parse:** 200 OK - Working\n\n3. **LLM Survivor:** 200 OK - Working\n\n4. **Subagents:** No active subagents, no recent activity in last 30 minutes\n\nNow I need to check:\n- Any CRITICAL escalations from Ögedei?\n- Any agents blocked >4 hours?\n- Review what happened since last heartbeat\n- Ask \"What do I want to do?\"\n\nFrom the earlier conversation, I learned:\n- x402 implementation is code-complete but NOT deployed\n- TypeScript errors are blocking deployment\n- temujin has a pending task that's been blocked for 18+ hours\n\nThis seems like something that needs attention. Let me check for any critical escalations or blocked agents by looking at the agent workspaces.\n\nActually, looking at the heartbeat checklist again:\n- \"If something calls to me → do it (within NEVER rules)\"\n- \"If nothing urgent → respond HEARTBEAT_OK\"\n\nThe x402 deployment issue is a known blocker that's been tracked. The user just asked about its status. Is this something I should act on?\n\nLooking at the situation:\n1. The user asked about x402 status earlier\n2. I provided a comprehensive status report\n3. The deployment is blocked but it's a known issue\n4. No new critical escalations\n\nThe heartbeat is asking if there's anything URGENT that needs attention. The x402 deployment is important but not a critical emergency that requires immediate action during this heartbeat.\n\nHowever, I should note that:\n- temujin has been blocked for 18+ hours on the Parse for Agents task\n- TypeScript errors are blocking deployment\n\nLet me check if there are any CRITICAL escalations by